avefaithinmassa00cooluoft |ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Coolidge |first=Calvin |title=Foundations of the Republic: Speeches and Addresses |publisher=University Press of the Pacific |year=2004 |origyear=1926 |isbn=978-1-4102-1598-7 |url=https://archive.org/stream/foundationsofrep00unit |ref={{sfnRef|Coolidge|1926}}}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Coolidge |first=Calvin |title=The Autobiography of Calvin Coolidge |publisher=Cosmopolitan Book Corp |year=1929 |isbn=978-0-944951-03-3 |url=https://archive.org/details/autobiographycal011459mbp |ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Coolidge |first=Calvin |title=The Quotable Calvin Coolidge: Sensible Words for a New Century |editor=Peter Hannaford |publisher=Images From The Past, Incorporated |year=2001 |isbn=978-1-884592-33-1 |ref={{sfnRef|Hannaford}}}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{Cite book |last=Coolidge |first=Calvin |title=The Talkative President: The Off-the Record Press Conferences of Calvin Coolidge |editor=Howard H. Quint and Robert H. Ferrell |publisher=[[University of Massachusetts Press]] |year=1964 |url=https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=77365439}}\n* {{cite book|last=Coolidge|first=Grace|authorlink=Grace Coolidge|editor1-last=Wikander|editor1-first=Lawrence E.|editor2-last=Ferrell|editor2-first=Robert H.|editor-link2=Robert Hugh Ferrell|title=Grace Coolidge: An Autobiography|url=https://archive.org/details/gracecoolidgeaut00cool|year=1992|publisher=High Plains Pub. Co.|lccn=92072825|isbn=978-1881019015}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ferrell|first=Robert H. |authorlink=Robert Hugh Ferrell|title= Grace Coolidge: The People's Lady in Silent Cal's White House |year=2008|lccn=2007045737 |isbn= 9780700615636}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Felzenberg |first=Alvin S. |date=Fall 1998 |title=Calvin Coolidge and Race: His Record in Dealing with the Racial Tensions of the 1920s |url=https://coolidgefoundation.org/resources/essays-papers-addresses-34/ |journal=New England Journal of History |volume=55 |issue=1 |pages=83\u201396}}\n*{{C