{"title_page": "Money Heist", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Money Heist\n| image                    = La casa de papel intertitle.png\n| caption                  = \n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|es|La casa de papel}} \n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Crime drama]]<ref name=nytimes_190719 />\n* [[Heist film|Heist]]<ref name=haaretz_180807 />\n* [[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]<ref name=antenacast />\n}}\n| creator                  = [[\u00c1lex Pina]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n<!-- Main and recurring are split and ordered as they appear in the series' credits. -->\n* [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]\n* [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]]\n* [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]\n* [[Paco Tous]]\n* [[Pedro Alonso]]\n* [[Alba Flores]]\n* [[Miguel Herr\u00e1n]]\n* [[Jaime Lorente]]\n* [[Esther Acebo]]\n* [[Enrique Arce]]\n* [[Mar\u00eda Pedraza]]\n* [[Darko Peri\u0107 (actor)|Darko Peri\u0107]]\n* [[Kiti M\u00e1nver]]\n* Hovik Keuchkerian\n* [[Rodrigo de la Serna]]\n* [[Najwa Nimri]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Manel Santisteban\n| opentheme                = \"My Life Is Going On\" by Cecilia Krull\n| composer                 = {{Plainlist|\n* Manel Santisteban\n* Iv\u00e1n Mart\u00ednez Lac\u00e1mara\n}}\n| country                  = Spain\n| language                 = Spanish\n| num_seasons              = <!-- READ: It is TWO seasons, but THREE aired parts as of August 2019.-->2 (3 parts){{efn|name=SeasonPart}}\n| num_episodes             = <!-- READ: The original release saw 15 episodes aired. Do not change this entry to the 30, which include the Netflix re-edited 22 episodes from part 1 and 2. -->23\n| list_episodes            = List of Money Heist episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* \u00c1lex Pina\n* Sonia Mart\u00ednez\n* Jes\u00fas Colmenar\n* Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato\n* Nacho Manubens\n}}\n| location                 = Madrid\n| cinematography           = Migue Amoedo\n| editor                   = {{Plainlist|\n* David Pelegr\u00edn\n* Luis Miguel Gonz\u00e1lez Bedmar\n* Ver\u00f3nica Call\u00f3n\n* Ra\u00fal Mora\n* Regino Hern\u00e1ndez\n* Raquel Marraco\n* Patricia Rubio\n}}\n| camera                   = Single-camera\n| runtime                  = 67\u201377 minutes (Antena 3)<br>41\u201357 minutes (Netflix)\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Vancouver Media\n* [[Atresmedia]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Netflix]]\n| picture_format           = {{Plainlist|\n1080p (16:9 HDTV)\n* 4K (16:9 UHDTV)\n}}\n| audio_format             = 5.1 surround sound\n| channel                  = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] (2017)\n* [[Netflix]] (2019)<!-- Netflix is the original network for part 3 in 2019. The first two parts in 2017 had Antena 3 as original network. -->\n}}\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2017|5|2|df=yes}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = https://www.netflix.com/title/80192098\n}}\n\n'''''Money Heist''''' ({{lang-es|'''La casa de papel'''}}, {{trans|The House of Paper}}) is a Spanish television [[heist genre|heist]] [[crime drama]] series. Created by [[\u00c1lex Pina]], the series was initially intended as a limited series to be told in two parts. It had its original run of 15 episodes on Spanish network [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] from 2 May 2017 through 23 November 2017. [[Netflix]] acquired the global streaming rights in late 2017. It re-cut the series into 22 shorter episodes and released them worldwide, beginning with the first part on 20 December 2017, followed by the second part on 6 April 2018. In April 2018, Netflix renewed the series with a significantly increased budget for 16 new episodes total. Part 3, with eight episodes, was released on 19 July 2019. Part 4, also with eight episodes, will be released on 3 April 2020. A documentary involving the producers and the cast will premiere on Netflix the same day, titled ''Money Heist: The Phenomenon''.\n\nThe first two parts revolve around a long-prepared, multi-day assault on the [[Royal Mint of Spain]] in [[Madrid]], in which a group of robbers take hostages as part of their plan to print and escape with \u20ac2.4 billion. It involves eight robbers, code-named after cities and led by the Professor ([[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]) from an external location. The story is primarily focused on one of the robbers, Tokyo ([[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]), as they battle with hostages on the inside and the police on the outside. In the third part, the surviving robbers are forced out of hiding, and with the help of new members, they plan and perform an assault on the [[Bank of Spain]].\n\nThe series was filmed in Madrid, Spain. Significant portions of part 3 were also filmed in [[Panama]], [[Thailand]] and [[Florence]], Italy. The narrative is told in a real-time-like fashion and relies on flashbacks, time-jumps, hidden character motivations and an unreliable narrator for complexity. The series subverts the heist genre by being told from the perspective of a woman (Tokyo) and having a strong [[Spaniard|Spanish]] identity, where emotional dynamics offset the perfect strategic crime.\n\nThe series received critical acclaim for its sophisticated plot, interpersonal dramas, direction and for trying to innovate Spanish television. The Italian anti-fascist song \"[[Bella ciao]]\", which plays multiple times throughout the series, became a summer hit across Europe in 2018. By 2018, the series was the most-watched non-English language series and one of the most-watched series overall on Netflix,<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> with a particular resonance coming from viewers from Mediterranean Europe and the Latin world.\n\n== Series overview ==\n{{main|List of Money Heist episodes}}\n{{:List of Money Heist episodes}}\n\n=== Season 1: Parts 1 and 2 (2017) ===\n\nPart 1 begins with the aftermath of a failed bank robbery by a woman named \"Tokyo\", as a man named the \"Professor\" saves her from being caught by the police and proposes her a heist of drastic proportions. After a brief outline of the planned heist, the story jumps to the beginning of a multi-day assault on the [[Royal Mint of Spain]] in [[Madrid]]. The eight robbers are code-named after cities: Tokyo, Moscow, Berlin, Nairobi, Rio, Denver, Helsinki and Oslo. Dressed in red jumpsuits with a mask of the Spanish painter [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]], the group of robbers take 67 hostages as part of their plan to print and escape with \u20ac2.4 billion through a self-built escape tunnel. The Professor heads the heist from an external location. Flashbacks throughout the series show the five months of preparation in an abandoned hunting estate in the [[Province of Toledo|Toledo]] countryside; the robbers are not to share personal information nor engage in personal relationships, and the assault shall be without bloodshed.\n\nThroughout parts 1 and 2, the robbers inside the Mint have difficulties sticking to the pre-defined rules, and face uncooperative hostages, violence, isolation, and mutiny. Tokyo commentates the events through [[voice-over]]s. While Denver pursues a love affair with the hostage M\u00f3nica Gaztambide, inspector Raquel Murillo of the [[National Police Corps]] negotiates with the Professor on the outside and begins an intimate relationship with his alter ego \"Salva\". The Professor's identity is repeatedly close to being uncovered, until Raquel realises his true identity, but is emotionally unable and unwilling to hand him over to the police. At the end of part 2, after 128 hours, the robbers escape successfully from the Mint with \u20ac984 million printed, but at the cost of the lives of Oslo, Moscow and Berlin. One year after the heist, Raquel decodes postcards left by the Professor for a location in [[Palawan]] in the Philippines, where she reunites with him.\n\n=== Season 2: Part 3 (2019) ===\n\nPart 3 begins two to three years after the heist on the Royal Mint of Spain, showing the robbers enjoying their lives paired-up in diverse locations. However, when [[Europol]] captures Rio with an intercepted phone, the Professor picks up Berlin's old plans to assault the [[Bank of Spain]] to force Europol to hand over Rio. He and Raquel (going by \"Lisbon\") get the gang, including M\u00f3nica (going by \"Stockholm\"), back together and enlist three new members: Bogot\u00e1, Palermo and Marseille. Flashbacks to the Professor and Berlin outline the planned new heist and their different approaches to love. The disguised robbers sneak into the heavily guarded bank, take hostages and eventually gain access to the gold and state secrets, while the Professor and Lisbon travel in an [[RV]] and then an ambulance while communicating with the robbers and the police. A breach in the bank is thwarted, forcing the police, led by Colonel Luis Tamayo and pregnant inspector Alicia Sierra, to release Rio to the robbers. Nairobi gets gravely injured by a police-inflicted [[sniper]] shot in the chest, and Lisbon is caught by the police. With another police assault on the bank incoming, and believing Lisbon to have been executed by the police, the Professor radios Palermo and declares [[DEFCON 2]] on the police. Part 3 concludes by showing Lisbon alive and in custody, and Tokyo narrating that the Professor had fallen for his own trap and that \"the war had begun.\"\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n\n=== Main ===\n<!-- Main and recurring are split and ordered as they appear in the series' credits. -->\n* [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]] as Silene Oliveira (Tokyo): the narrator; she was a runaway robber until scouted by the Professor to participate in his plan.\n* [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]] as Raquel Murillo (Lisbon): an inspector of the [[National Police Corps]] who is put in charge of the case until she joins the group in part 3.\n* [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]] as Sergio Marquina (The Professor / Salvador \"Salva\" Mart\u00edn): the mastermind of the heist who assembled the group, and Berlin's brother.\n* [[Paco Tous]] as Agust\u00edn Ramos (Moscow) (part 1\u20132; featured part 3): a former miner turned criminal and Denver's father.\n* [[Pedro Alonso]] as Andr\u00e9s de Fonollosa (Berlin): a terminally ill jewel thief and the Professor's second-in-command and brother.\n* [[Alba Flores]] as \u00c1gata Jim\u00e9nez (Nairobi): an expert in forgery in charge of printing the money for the group.\n* [[Miguel Herr\u00e1n]] as An\u00edbal Cort\u00e9s (Rio): a young hacker and Tokyo's boyfriend.\n* [[Jaime Lorente]] as Daniel/Ricardo{{efn|The official website lists Denver's name as Daniel,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/noticias/conoce-los-verdaderos-nombres-de-la-banda-de-atracadores-de-la-casa-de-papel_201711255a1940100cf2f56e3ec268dd.html |title=Conoce los verdaderos nombres de la banda de atracadores de 'La casa de papel' |language=es |publisher=antena3.com |last=\u00c1lvarez |first=Jennifer |date=25 November 2017 |access-date=16 August 2019}}</ref> but in the show he has called himself Ricardo.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Part 2, episode 8 |series=Money Heist |network=Netflix <!--|season= |series-no= |number=--> |time=36:50 |quote= |language=}}</ref>}} Ramos (Denver): Moscow's son who joins him in the heist.\n* [[Esther Acebo]] as M\u00f3nica Gaztambide (Stockholm): one of the hostages who is Arturo Rom\u00e1n's secretary and mistress, carrying his child out of wedlock. During the robbery, she falls in love with Denver and becomes an accomplice to the group.\n* [[Enrique Arce]] as Arturo Rom\u00e1n: a hostage and the Director of the [[Royal Mint of Spain]].\n* [[Mar\u00eda Pedraza]] as Alison Parker (part 1\u20132): a hostage and daughter of the British ambassador to Spain.\n* [[Darko Peri\u0107 (actor)|Darko Peri\u0107]] as Yashin Das\u00e1yev (Helsinki): a veteran Serbian soldier and Oslo's cousin.\n* [[Kiti M\u00e1nver]] as Mariv\u00ed Fuentes (part 1\u20132; featured part 3): Raquel's mother.\n* Hovik Keuchkerian as Bogot\u00e1 (part 3): an expert in metallurgy who joins the robbery of the [[Bank of Spain]].\n* [[Rodrigo de la Serna]] as Mart\u00edn (Palermo / The Engineer) (part 3): an old friend of Berlin's who planned the robbery of the Bank of Spain with him and assumes his place as commanding officer.\n* [[Najwa Nimri]] as Alicia Sierra (part 3): a pregnant inspector of the National Police Corps put in charge of the case after Raquel's departure from the force.\n\n=== Recurring ===\n* Roberto Garcia Ruiz as Dimitri Mostov\u00f3i / Radko Dragi\u0107{{efn|The final closing credits reveal Oslo's [[mug shot]] with the name Dimitri Mostov\u00f3i,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Part 2, episode 9 |series=Money Heist |network=Netflix <!--|season= |series-no= |number=--> |time=43:50 |quote= |language=}}</ref> while his coffin shows the name Radko Dragic.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Part 2, episode 8 |series=Money Heist |network=Netflix <!--|season= |series-no= |number=--> |time=24:00 |quote= |language=}}</ref>}} (Oslo) (part 1\u20132; featured part 3): a veteran Serbian soldier and Helsinki's cousin.\n* [[Fernando Soto (Spanish actor)|Fernando Soto]] as \u00c1ngel Rubio: a deputy inspector and Raquel's second-in-command.\n* Juan Fern\u00e1ndez as Colonel Prieto: a member of the Spanish Intelligence who oversees Raquel's work on the case.\n* Anna Gras as Mercedes Colmenar (part 1\u20132): Alison's teacher and one of the hostages.\n* Fran Morcillo as Pablo Ruiz (part 1): Alison's schoolmate and one of the hostages.\n* Clara Alvarado as Ariadna Cascales (part 1\u20132): one of the hostages who works in the Mint.\n* Mario de la Rosa as Su\u00e1rez: the chief of the [[Grupo Especial de Operaciones]].\n* Miquel Garc\u00eda Borda as Alberto Vicu\u00f1a (part 1\u20132): Raquel's ex-husband and a forensic examiner.\n* Naia Guz as Paula Vicu\u00f1a Murillo: Raquel and Alberto's daughter.\n* Luka Peros as Marseille (part 3): a member of the gang who joins the robbery of the Bank of Spain.\n* Fernando Cayo as Colonel Luis Tamayo (part 3): a member of the Spanish Intelligence who oversees Alicia's work on the case.\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Conception and writing ===\n\n{{further|#Themes and analysis}}\n\n{{Quote box |title= |quote=\"We wanted to make a very small project in a simple way; we wanted to cross lines we couldn't cross in previous projects, in terms of narrative and structure without any intermediaries.\" |author=\u2014Writer Esther Martinez Lobato |source=October 2018<ref name=dramaquarterly_181015 /> |align=right |width=30% |bgcolor=lightblue }}\n\nThe series was conceived by screenwriter [[\u00c1lex Pina]] and director Jes\u00fas Colmenar during their years of collaboration since 2008.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> After finishing their work on the Spanish prison drama [[Locked Up (TV series)|''Vis a vis'' (''Locked Up'')]], they left Globomedia to set up their own production company, named Vancouver Media, in 2016.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /><ref name=elespanol_170522>{{cite web |last=Jabonero |first=Daniel |url=https://www.elespanol.com/bluper/noticias/dificultades-fox-producir-tercera-temporada-vis-a-vis |title=Las dificultades que tiene FOX para producir una tercera temporada de \u2018Vis a Vis\u2019 |language=es |publisher=elespanol.com |date=22 May 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> For their first project, they considered either filming a comedy or developing a heist story for television,<ref name=elperiodico_190718>{{cite web |last=Fern\u00e1ndez |first=Juan |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/tele/20190718/la-casa-papel-somos-frikis-7557292 |title=Los de 'La casa de papel' somos unos frikis |language=es |publisher=elperiodico.com |date=18 July 2019 |access-date=17 August 2019}}</ref> with the latter having never been attempted before on Spanish television.<ref name=elconfidencial_170103>{{cite web |last=Galv |first=Marian |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-01-03/la-casa-de-papel-ursula-corbero-alba-flores-miguel-herran-paco-tous_1311689/ |title='La Casa de Papel' ficha a \u00darsula Corber\u00f3, Alba flores, Miguel Herr\u00e1n y Paco Tous |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=3 January 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref>  Along with former ''Locked Up'' colleagues,{{efn|''Locked Up'' and ''Money Heist'' share \u00c1lex Pina, Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato, Pablo Roa, and Esther Morales as writers; and Jes\u00fas Colmenar and Alex Rodrigo as directors.}} they developed ''Money Heist'' as a passion project to try new things without outside interference.<ref name=dramaquarterly_181015>{{cite web |url=https://dramaquarterly.com/pier-pressure/ |title=Pier pressure |publisher=dramaquarterly.com |date=15 October 2018 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref> Pina was firm about making it a limited series, feeling that dilution had become a problem for his previous productions.<ref name=elmundo_171016 />\n\nInitially entitled ''Los Desahuciados'' ({{transl|es|IAST|The Evicted}}) in the conception phase,<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> the series was developed to subvert heist conventions and combine elements of the [[action genre]], [[thrillers]] and [[surrealism]], while still being credible.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> Pina saw an advantage over typical heist films in that character development could span a considerably longer narrative arc.<ref name=partiv>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/global/money-heist-la-casa-de-papel-creator-alex-pina-10-takes-part-3-2-1203267428/|title=\u2018Money Heist\u2019 \u2013 \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 \u2013 Creator Alex Pina: 10 Takes on Part 3 |publisher=variety.com |last2=Hopewell |first2=John |last=Lang |first=Jamie |date=15 July 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> Characters were to be shown from multiple sides to break the viewers' preconceptions of villainy and retain their interest throughout the show.<ref name=partiv /> Key aspects of the planned storyline were written down at the beginning,<ref name=elmundo_190719>{{cite web |last=Elidrissi |first=Fati |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2019/07/19/5d30b25ffc6c83400d8b4622.html |title=La casa de papel: el fen\u00f3meno global espa\u00f1ol que retroalimenta la ficci\u00f3n |language=es |publisher=elmundo.es |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> while the finer story beats were developed incrementally to not overwhelm the writers.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander compared the writing process to the Professor's way of thinking, \"going around, writing down options, consulting engineers whom you cannot tell why you ask them that\", but noted that fiction allowed the police to be written dumber when necessary.<ref name=elmundo_190912 />\n\nThe beginning of filming was set for January 2017,<ref name=elconfidencial_170103 /> allowing for five months of pre-production.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The narrative was split into two parts for financial considerations.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The robbers' city-based code names, which Spanish newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' compared to the colour-based code names in [[Quentin Tarantino]]'s 1992 heist film ''[[Reservoir Dogs]]'',<ref name=abc_190716>{{cite web |last=Jim\u00e9nez |first=Alex |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-casa-papel-claves-exito-imparable-casa-papel-triunfa-todo-mundo-mano-netflix-201907160132_noticia.html |title=Las claves del \u00e9xito imparable de \"La casa de papel\", que triunfa en todo el mundo de la mano de Netflix |language=es |publisher=elperiodico.com |date=16 July 2019 |access-date=22 September 2019}}</ref> were chosen at random in the first part,<ref name=elperiodico_190627>{{cite web |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/yotele/20190627/netflix-confirma-cuarta-temporada-casa-papel-7524435 |title=Netflix confirma la cuarta temporada de 'La casa de papel' |language=es |publisher=[[El Peri\u00f3dico de Catalunya|elperiodico.com]] |date=27 June 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> although places with high viewership resonance were also taken into account for the new robbers' code names in part 3.<ref name=xataka_190705 /> The first five lines of the pilot script took a month to write,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> as the writers were unable to make the Professor or Moscow work as narrator.<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> Tokyo as an [[unreliable narrator]], flashbacks and time-jumps increased the narrative complexity,<ref name=partiv /> but also made the story more fluid for the audience.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The pilot episode required over 50 script versions until the producers were satisfied.<ref name=elpais_lcdp /><ref name=lanacion_190616>{{cite web |last=Ventura |first=Laura |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/de-visita-en-el-rodaje-de-la-nueva-casa-de-papel-nid2257022 |title=De visita en el rodaje de la nueva Casa de papel |language=es |publisher=lanacion.com.ar |date=16 June 2019 |access-date=23 September 2019}}</ref> Later scripts would be finished once per week to keep up with filming.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 />\n\n=== Casting ===\nCasting took place late in 2016, spanning more than two months.<ref name=abc_170628 /> The characters were not fully fleshed out at the beginning of this process, and took shape based on the actors' performance.<ref name=tercer_grado /> Casting directors Eva Leira and Yolanda Serrano were looking for actors with the ability to play empathetic robbers with believable love and family connections.<ref name=20minutos_190204>{{cite web |url=https://www.20minutos.com.mx/noticia/476793/0/eva-leira-y-yolanda-serrano-buscan-el-alma-del-actor-para-sus-series |title=Eva Leira y Yolanda Serrano buscan el alma del actor para sus series |publisher=[[20minutos]].com.mx |language=es |date=4 February 2019 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref> Antena 3 announced the ensemble cast in March 2017<ref name=antenacast>{{cite web |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/noticias/ursula-corbero-alba-flores-alvaro-morte-protagonistas-fiction-stories-%E2%80%98la-casa-papel%E2%80%99_2017032158d17ba20cf201b3e54261b1.html |title=\u00darsula Corber\u00f3, Alba Flores and \u00c1lvaro Morte, protagonists of the fiction stories of 'La Casa de Papel' |website=antena3.com |date=21 March 2017 |accessdate=20 August 2019 |language=es}}</ref> and released audition excerpts of most cast actors in the series' aftershow ''Tercer Grado'' and on their website.<ref name=tercer_grado />\n\nThe Professor was designed as a charismatic yet shy villain who could convince the robbers to follow him and make the audience sympathetic to the robbers' resistance against the powerful banks.<ref name=laprensa_190809>{{cite web |last=Ruiz de Elvira |first=\u00c1lvaro |url=https://laprensa.peru.com/espectaculos/noticia-casa-papel-parte-3-fecha-estreno-netflix-y-todo-lo-que-se-sabe-hasta-ahora-temporada-3-nnda-lt-78426 |title=La Casa de Papel, temporada 3: fecha de estreno en Netflix, tr\u00e1iler, historia, sinopsis, personajes, actores y todo sobre la Parte 3 |language=es |publisher=laprensa.peru.com |date=13 July 2018 |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref> However, developing the Professor's role proved difficult, as the character did not follow archetypal conventions<ref name=abc_170628 /> and the producers were uncertain about his degree of brilliance.<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> While the producers found his Salva personality early on,<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> they were originally looking for a 50-year-old [[Harvard]] professor type with the looks of Spanish actor [[Jos\u00e9 Coronado]].<ref name=esquire_190125 /><ref name=elmundo_171016 /> The role was proposed to [[Javier Guti\u00e9rrez \u00c1lvarez|Javier Guti\u00e9rrez]], but he was already committed to starring in the film ''[[Champions (2018 film)|Campeones]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-actor-realidad-iba-profesor-lugar-alvaro-morte-nnda-nnlt-noticia-681470-noticia/ |title=\"La casa de papel\": \u00bfqui\u00e9n es el actor que en realidad iba a ser el Profesor en lugar de \u00c1lvaro Morte? |language=es |publisher=elcomercio.pe |date=5 November 2019 |accessdate=6 November 2019}}</ref> Meanwhile, the casting directors advocated for [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]], whom they knew from their collaboration on the long-running Spanish soap opera ''[[El secreto de Puente Viejo]]'', even though his prime time television experience was limited at that point.<ref name=esquire_190125>{{cite web |last=P\u00e9rez |first=Ana |url=https://www.esquire.com/es/actualidad/tv/a26006005/alvaro-morte-la-casa-de-papel-3-temporada-el-embarcadero/ |title=Hablamos de series con 'El profesor' \u00c1lvaro Morte |language=es |publisher=esquire.com |date=25 January 2019 |accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref> Going through the full casting process and approaching the role through external analysis rather than personal experience, Morte described the professor as \"a tremendous box of surprises\" that \"end up shaping this character because he never ceases to generate uncertainty\", making it unclear for the audience if the character is good or bad.<ref name=abc_170628 /> The producers also found that his appearance of a primary school teacher gave the character more credibility.<ref name=elmundo_171016 />\n\n[[Pedro Alonso]] was cast to play Berlin, whom ''[[La Voz de Galicia]]'' would later characterize as a \"cold, hypnotic, sophisticated and disturbing character, an inveterate macho with serious empathy problems, a white-collar thief who despises his colleagues and considers them inferior.\"<ref name=lavozdegalicia_170503 /> The actor's portrayal of the character was inspired by a chance encounter Alonso had the day before receiving his audition script, with \"an intelligent person\" who was \"provocative or even manipulative\" to him.<ref name=lefigaro_180621>{{cite web |last=Perrin |first=\u00c9lisabeth |url=http://tvmag.lefigaro.fr/programme-tv/pedro-alonso-la-casa-de-papel-berlin-est-a-la-fois-cruel-heroique-et-drole-_88de13be-749a-11e8-8a00-24b61b86dc61/ |title=Pedro Alonso (La casa de papel) : \"Berlin est \u00e0 la fois cruel, h\u00e9ro\u00efque et dr\u00f4le\" |language=fr |publisher=lefigaro.fr |date=21 June 2018 |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref> Alonso saw high observation skills and an unusual understanding of his surroundings in Berlin, resulting in unconventional and unpredictable character behaviour.<ref name=lavozdegalicia_170503>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/television/2017/05/03/casa-papel-berlin/00031493797995350336283.htm |title=\"La casa de papel\": \u00bfQui\u00e9n es Berl\u00edn? |language=es |publisher=lavozdegalicia.es |date=3 May 2017 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref> Similarities between Berlin and [[Najwa Nimri]]'s character Zulema in Pina's TV series ''[[Locked Up (TV series)|Locked Up]]'' were unintentional.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/20170509/422415395188/la-casa-de-papel-antena-3-alex-pina.html |title=\u00bfC\u00f3mo se planifica el atraco perfecto de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019? |language=es |publisher=lavanguardia.com |date=9 May 2017 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref> The family connections between the Professor and Berlin were not in the original script, but were built into the characters' backstory at the end of part 1 after Morte and Alonso had repeatedly proposed to do so.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bravo |first=Vict\u00f3ria |url=https://www.metrojornal.com.br/entretenimento/2019/08/06/la-casa-de-papel-atores-revelam-como-mudaram-o-futuro-da-serie-mesmo-sem-o-consentimento-dos-criadores.html |title=La Casa de Papel: Atores revelam como mudaram o futuro da s\u00e9rie mesmo sem o consentimento dos criadores |language=pt |publisher=metrojornal.com.br |date=6 August 2019 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe producers found the protagonist and narrator, Tokyo, among the hardest characters to develop,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629>{{cite web |last=Pickard |first=Michael |url=https://dramaquarterly.com/hold-up/ |title=Right on the Money |publisher=dramaquarterly.com |date=29 June 2018 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref> as they were originally looking for an older actress to play the character who had nothing to lose before meeting the Professor.<ref name=tercer_grado/> [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]] eventually landed the role for bringing a playful energy to the table; her voice was heavily factored in during casting, as she was the first voice the audience hears in the show.<ref name=tercer_grado /> [[Jaime Lorente]] developed Denver's hallmark laughter during the casting process.<ref name=tercer_grado /> Two cast actors had appeared in previous TV series by \u00c1lex Pina: [[Paco Tous]] (Moscow) had starred in the 2010 TV series ''[[Los hombres de Paco]]'', and [[Alba Flores]] (Nairobi) had starred starred in ''Locked Up''. Flores was asked to play Nairobi without audition when Pina realized late in the conception phase that the show needed another female gang member.<ref name=elmundo_171016>{{cite web |last=Gasparyan |first=Suren |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2017/10/16/59e22acf468aeb9c3f8b45d5.html |title=Una 'casa de papel' con dos 'profesores' |language=es |publisher=elmundo.es |date=16 October 2017 |accessdate=13 September 2019}}</ref> For the role opposite to the robbers, [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]] was cast to play Inspector Raquel Murillo, whom Itu\u00f1o described as a \"strong and powerful woman in a world of men, but also sensitive in her private life\".<ref name=repubblica_180923>{{cite web |last=Echites |first=Giulia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/serie/2018/09/23/news/l_ispettor_murillo_de_la_casa_di_carta_la_mia_raquel_donna_forte_in_un_mondo_di_uomini_-207157309/ |title=L'ispettore Murillo de 'La casa di carta': \"La mia Raquel, donna forte in un mondo di uomini\" |language=it |publisher=repubblica.it |date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=30 September 2019}}</ref> She took inspiration from ''[[The Silence of the Lambs (novel)|The Silence of the Lambs]]'' character [[Clarice Starling]], an FBI student with a messy family life who develops sympathies for a criminal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wradio.com.co/noticias/sociedad/la-tercera-parte-de-la-serie-sera-un-bombazo-itziar-ituno-actriz-de-la-casa-de-papel/20180418/nota/3738979.aspx |title=La tercera parte de la serie ser\u00e1 un \"bombazo\": Itziar Itu\u00f1o, actriz de \"La casa de papel\" |language=es |publisher=wradio.com.co |date=18 April 2018 |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe actors learned of the show's renewal by Netflix before the producers contacted them to return.<ref>{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Livia |url=https://rpp.pe/tv/netflix/la-casa-de-papel-itziar-ituno-confirma-que-raquel-murillo-estara-en-la-tercera-temporada-noticia-1134985 |title=\"La Casa de Papel\": Itziar Itu\u00f1o confirma que Raquel Murillo estar\u00e1 en la tercera temporada |website=[[as.com]] |date=9 July 2018 |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref> In October 2018, Netflix announced the cast of part 3; the returning main cast included Pedro Alonso, raising speculation about his role in part 3.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/global/la-casa-de-papel-part-3-production-watch-video-1202993850/ |publisher=variety.com |title=\u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 Part 3 Goes into Production: Watch Video |date=25 October 2018 |accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> Among the new cast members were Argentine actor [[Rodrigo de la Serna]], who saw a possible connection between his character's name and the Argentine football legend [[Mart\u00edn Palermo]],<ref>{{cite web |first=\u00c1. |last= Jim\u00e9nez |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-casa-papel-motivo-palermo-llama-casa-papel-201907300136_noticia.html |title=El motivo por el que Palermo se llama as\u00ed en \"La casa de papel\" |website=abc.es |date=30 July 2019 |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref> and ''Locked Up'' star Najwa Nimri. Cameo scenes of Brazilian football star, and fan of the series, [[Neymar]], as a monk were filmed for part 3, but were excluded from the stream without repercussions to the narrative until judicial charges against him had been dropped in late August 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Galarraga Gort\u00e1zar |first=Naiara |url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2019/09/04/inenglish/1567586223_216483.html |title=Neymar makes cameo in Netflix hit \u2018Money Heist\u2019 after rape case dropped |website=elpais.com |date=4 September 2019 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=elmundo_190912 /> A small appearance by Spanish actress [[Bel\u00e9n Cuesta]] in two episodes of part 3 raised fan and media speculation about her role in part 4.<ref>{{cite web |first=V\u00edctor |last=Mill\u00e1n |url=https://as.com/epik/2019/08/04/portada/1564907334_831996.html |title='La Casa de Papel': \u00bfQu\u00e9 significa el papel de 'extra' de Bel\u00e9n Cuesta? |website=[[as.com]] |date=5 August 2019 |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Production design ===\n\n[[File:Salvador Dali NYWTS.jpg|thumb|upright|Spanish Surrealist painter [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]] was chosen as the heist team's mask design.]]\n\nThe show's look and atmosphere were developed by creator \u00c1lex Pina, director Jes\u00fas Colmenar, and director of photography Migue Amoedo, according to ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' \"the most prolific television trio in recent years\".<ref name=lavanguardia_190719>{{cite web |last=Sol\u00e0 Gimferrer |first=Pere |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/netflix/20190719/463580297705/la-casa-de-papel-claves-exito-serie-netflix.html |title=Las claves del \u00e9xito de La casa de papel |language=es |publisher=lavanguardia.com |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> Abd\u00f3n Alca\u00f1iz served as art director.<ref name=alicanteplaza_180612 /> Their collaboration projects usually take a primary colour as a basis;<ref name=alicanteplaza_180612>{{cite web |last=Vi\u00f1as |first=Eugenio |url=https://alicanteplaza.es/AbdnAlcaizelvalencianotrasladireccindeartedealgunasdelasgrandesseriesespaolas |title=Abd\u00f3n Alca\u00f1iz, el valenciano tras la direcci\u00f3n de arte de algunas de las grandes series espa\u00f1olas |language=es |publisher=elpais.com |date=12 June 2018 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> ''Money Heist'' had red as \"one of the distinguishing features of the series\"<ref name=elpais_170503 /> that stood over the gray sets.<ref name=elpais_190711 /> Blue, green and yellow were marked as a forbidden colour in production design.<ref name=elpais_190711>{{Cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/07/11/television/1562847443_895744.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 derrocha poder\u00edo en su regreso |language=es |date=12 July 2019 |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=elpais.com |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> To achieve \"absolute film quality\", red tones were tested with different types of fabrics, textures and lighting.<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> The iconography of the robbers' red jumpsuits mirrored the yellow prison dress code in ''Locked Up''.<ref name=elpais_170503>{{cite web |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2017/05/03/television/1493765342_705803.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 se atreve |language=es |publisher=elpais.com |date=3 May 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> For part 3, the Italian retail clothing company [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]] modified the red jumpsuits to better fit the body and launched a clothing line inspired by the series.<ref name=elpais_190711 /> [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]] was chosen as the robbers' mask design because of Dal\u00ed's recognisable visage that also serves as an iconic cultural reference to Spain; [[Don Quixote]] as an alternative mask design was discarded.<ref name=elpais_180712>{{cite web |last=Ruiz de Elvira |first=\u00c1lvaro |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2018/07/12/television/1531403342_602750.html |title=\u00c1lex Pina: \"Hay que hacer avances en la ficci\u00f3n, el espectador es cada vez m\u00e1s experto\" |language=es |publisher=elpais.com |date=13 July 2018 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> This choice sparked criticism by the [[Gala-Salvador Dal\u00ed Foundation]] for not requesting the necessary permissions.<ref name=20minutos_190204 />\n\nTo make the plot more realistic, the producers requested and received advice from the national police and the Spanish Ministry of Interior.<ref name=elmundo_170502 /><ref>{{cite web |last=Molina |first=Berto |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-05-08/casa-de-papel-serie-antena-3-fabrica-nacional-moneda-timbre-atraco_1379218/ |title=La F\u00e1brica de la Moneda, molesta con la trama de la serie 'La casa de papel' |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=8 May 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> The robbers' banknotes were printed with permission of the [[Bank of Spain]] and had an increased size as an anti-counterfeit measure.<ref name=elmundo_170502>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2017/05/02/59077570ca474185328b463d.html |title=Todo el dinero de La casa de papel |language=es |date=2 May 2017 |last=Gago |first=Claudia |website=elmundo.es |access-date=9 September 2019}}</ref> The greater financial backing of Netflix for part 3 allowed for the build of over 50 sets across five basic filming locations world-wide.<ref name=publimetro_190711 /> Preparing a remote and uninhabited island in [[Panama]] to represent a robber hide-out proved difficult, as it needed to be cleaned, secured and built on, and involved hours-long travelling with material transportation.<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> The real Bank of Spain was unavailable for visiting and filming for security reasons, so the producers recreated the Bank on a two-level stage by their own imagining, taking inspiration from Spanish architecture of the [[Francisco Franco]] era.<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> Publicly available information was used to make the Bank's main hall set similar to the real location. The other interior sets were inspired by different periods and artificially aged to accentuate the building's history.<ref name=publimetro_190711 /> [[Bronze]] and [[granite]] sculptures and motifs from the [[Valle de los Ca\u00eddos]] were recreated for the interior,<ref name=sensacine_190617>{{cite web |last=Romero |first=Marta A. |url=http://www.sensacine.com/noticias/series/noticia-18577464/ |title='La casa de papel' nos abre sus puertas: te contamos c\u00f3mo se ha rodado la tercera temporada con Netflix |language=es |publisher=sensacine.com |date=17 June 2019 |access-date=18 September 2019}}</ref> and over 50 paintings were painted for the Bank to emulate the [[Ateneo de Madrid]].<ref name=publimetro_190711>{{cite web |last=Cordovez |first=Karen |url=https://www.publimetro.cl/cl/entretenimiento/2019/07/11/la-casa-papel-los-secretos-del-rodaje-la-tercera-temporada.html |title=\"La Casa de Papel\": los secretos del rodaje de la tercera temporada |language=es |publisher=publimetro.cl |date=11 July 2019 |access-date=18 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n\n[[File:Edificio central del CSIC (Madrid) 02.jpg|thumb|right|240px|The [[Spanish National Research Council]] headquarters, the principal filming location of part 1 and 2 of ''Money Heist'']]\n[[File:Madrid - Nuevos Ministerios 03.JPG|thumb|right|240px|The [[Nuevos Ministerios]], the principal filming location of part 3 of ''Money Heist'']]\n\nParts 1 and 2 were filmed back-to-back in the greater [[Madrid]] region from January until August 2017.<ref name=abc_170628 /><ref name=lavanguardia_190807>{{Cite web |first=Molly |last=Antigone Hall |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/ocio/viajes/20190807/463750726691/lugares-rodaje-casa-de-papel.html |title=Este es el Madrid real de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |date=7 August 2019 |website=lavanguardia.com |access-date=9 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=elpais_lcdp /> The pilot episode was recorded in 26 days,<ref name=elmundo_170502 /> while all other episodes had around 14 filming days.<ref name=partiv/> Production was split into two units to save time, with one unit shooting scenes involving the Professor and the police, and the other filming scenes with the robbers.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The main storyline is set in the [[Royal Mint (Spain)|Royal Mint of Spain]] in Madrid, but the exterior scenes were filmed at the [[Spanish National Research Council]] (CSIC) headquarters for its passing resemblance to the Mint,<ref name=elmundo_170502 /> and on the roof of the Higher Technical School of Aeronautical Engineers, part of the [[Technical University of Madrid]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190807 /> The hunting estate where the robbers plan their coup was filmed at the Finca El Gasco farm estate in [[Torrelodones]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190807 /> Interior filming took place at the former ''[[Locked Up (TV series)|Locked Up]]'' sets in [[Colmenar Viejo]]<ref name=elespanol_170522 /> and at the Spanish national daily newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' in [[Torrej\u00f3n de Ardoz]] for printing press scenes.<ref name=elpais_lcdp>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elpais.com.co/especiales/la-casa-de-papel/ |title=La historia detr\u00e1s del \u00e9xito |language=es |website=elpais.com.co |access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref> As the show was designed as a limited series, all sets were destroyed once production of part 2 had finished.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 />\n\nParts 3 and 4 were also filmed back-to-back,<ref name=elcomercio_190808 /> with 21 to 23 filming days per episode.<ref name=partiv/> Netflix announced the start of filming on 25 October 2018,<ref name=laprensa_190809 /> and filming of part 4 ended in August 2019.<ref name=p4filmend /> In 2018, Netflix had opened their first European production hub in [[Tres Cantos]] near Madrid for new and existing Netflix productions;<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hopewell |first=John |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/netflix-european-production-hub-madrid-1202882341/ |title=Netflix Launches Its First European Production Hub in Madrid |date=24 July 2018 |website=elpais.com |access-date=10 September 2019}}</ref> main filming moved there onto a set three times the size of the set used for parts 1 and 2.<ref name=elpais_190614 /> The main storyline is set in the [[Bank of Spain]] in Madrid, but the exterior was filmed at the Ministry of Development complex [[Nuevos Ministerios]].<ref name=elpais_190614>{{Cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/06/14/television/1560524898_475068.html |title=\"La serie es m\u00e1s grande\": dentro de la nueva temporada de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |date=17 June 2019 |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=elpais.com |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> A scene where money is dropped from the sky was filmed at [[Callao Square]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190807 /> {{Interlanguage link|Ermita de San Frutos|es|Ermita de San Frutos (Carrascal del R\u00edo)}} in [[Carrascal del R\u00edo]] served as the exterior of the Italian monastery where the robbers plan the heist.<ref name=elpais_190711 /> The motorhome scenes of the Professor and Lisboa were filmed at the deserted Las Salinas beaches in [[Almer\u00eda]] to make the audience feel that the characters are safe from the police although their exact location is undisclosed at first.<ref name=lavanguardia_191117 /> Underwater scenes inside the vault were filmed at [[Pinewood Studios]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite AV media |people=Flores, Alba |date=4 October 2019 |title=Escena Favorita: Alba Flores \u2013 La Casa de Papel \u2013 Netflix |language=es |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=glP9VPzxZnY |access-date=7 October 2019 |time=0:30 |publisher= La Casa De Papel at youtube.com}}</ref><ref name=xataka_190705 /> The beginning of part 3 was also filmed in [[Thailand]], on the [[Guna Yala]] islands in [[Panama]], and in [[Florence]], Italy,<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> which helped to counter the claustrophobic feeling of the first two parts,<ref name=partiv /> but was also an expression of the plot's global repercussions.<ref name=elespectador_190718 />\n\n=== Music ===\n\nThe series' theme song, \"My Life Is Going On\", was composed by Manel Santisteban, who also served as composer on ''Locked Up''. Santisteban approached Spanish singer Cecilia Krull to write and perform the lyrics, which are about having confidence in one's abilities and the future.<ref name=oprahmag_190722>{{cite web |url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a28468639/la-casa-de-papel-money-heist-theme-song/ |title=The Theme Song for Netflix's La Casa de Papel/Money Heist Sends a Deliberate Message |date=22 July 2019 |last=Fernandez |first=Celia |publisher=oprahmag.com |access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref> The theme song is played behind a title sequence featuring paper models of major settings from the series.<ref name=oprahmag_190722 /> Krull's main source of inspiration was the character Tokyo in the first episode of the series, when the Professor offers her a way out of a desperate moment.<ref name=lavoz_190917 /> The lyrics are in English as the language that came naturally to Krull at the time of writing.<ref name=lavoz_190917>{{cite web |url=https://vos.lavoz.com.ar/musica/cecilia-krull-la-voz-por-detras-de-la-cancion-de-la-casa-de-papel |title=Cecilia Krull, la voz por detr\u00e1s de la canci\u00f3n de \"La casa de papel\" |date=17 September 2019 |last=Rojas |first=Rodrigo |publisher=vos.lavoz.com.ar |language=es |access-date=25 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Italian [[anti-fascist]] song \"[[Bella ciao]]\" plays multiple times throughout the series and accompanies two emblematic key scenes: At the end of the first part the Professor and Berlin sing it in preparation for the heist, embracing themselves as resistance against the establishment,<ref name=faz_180802>{{Cite web |url=https://www.faz.net/aktuell/gesellschaft/menschen/bella-ciao-und-die-netflix-serie-haus-des-geldes-15719916.html |title=\"Wie \"Bella Ciao\" zum Sommerhit wurde |language=de |last=Wiesner |first=Maria |date=2 August 2018 |access-date=14 August 2019 |publisher=[[faz.net]]}}</ref> and in the second part it plays during the thieves' escape from the Mint, as a metaphor for freedom.<ref name=\"bellaciao\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vix.com/pt/series/555595/bella-ciao-musica-em-la-casa-de-papel-e-antiga-mas-tem-tudo-a-ver-com-a-serie |title=\"Bella Ciao\": m\u00fasica em \"La Casa de Papel\" \u00e9 antiga, mas tem TUDO a ver com a s\u00e9rie |language=pt |date=19 February 2018 |last=Pereira |first=Alien |publisher=vix.com |access-date=14 August 2019}}</ref> Regarding the use of the song, Tokyo recounts in one of her narrations, \"The life of the Professor revolved around a single idea: Resistance. His grandfather, who had [[Italian resistance movement|fought against the fascists in Italy]], taught him the song and he taught us.\"<ref name=\"bellaciao\" /> The song was brought to the show by writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander. He had listened to \"Bella ciao\" at home to cheer him up, as he had grown frustrated for not finding a suitable song for the middle of part 1.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> He was aware of the song's meaning and history and felt it represented positive values.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> \"Bella ciao\" became a summer hit in Europe in 2018, mostly due to the popularity of the series and not the song's grave themes.<ref name=faz_180802 />\n\n== Themes and analysis ==\n\nThe series was noted for its subversions of the [[heist genre]]. While heist films are usually told with a rational male Anglo-centric focus, the series reframes the heist story by giving it a strong [[Spaniard|Spanish]] identity and telling it from a female perspective through Tokyo.<ref name=lavozdeasturias_190126>{{cite web |last=Vidal |first=Mar\u00eda |url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/cultura/2019/01/26/embarcadero-tenia-presion-casa-papel/0003_201901SY26P14991.htm |title=\u00c1lex Pina: \"Con 'El embarcadero' ten\u00eda m\u00e1s presi\u00f3n que con 'La Casa de Papel'\" |language=es |publisher=lavozdeasturias.es |date=4 February 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> The producers regarded the cultural identity as an important part of the personality of the series, as it made the story more relatable for viewers.<ref name=xataka_190705>{{cite web |last=Muela |first=Cesar |url=https://www.xataka.com/cine-y-tv/casa-papel-no-hubiera-estado-netflix-seguiriamos-diciendo-que-no-podemos-competir-series-fuera-alex-pina-creador-serie |title=\"Si 'La Casa de Papel' no hubiera estado en Netflix seguir\u00edamos diciendo que no podemos competir con las series de fuera\", \u00c1lex Pina, creador de la serie |publisher=xataka.com |language=es |date=3 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> They also avoided adapting the series to international tastes,<ref name=xataka_190705 /> which helped to set it apart from the usual American TV series<ref name=elespanol_190724 /> and raised international awareness of Spanish sensibilities.<ref name=xataka_190705 /> Emotional dynamics like the passion and impulsivity of friendship and love offset the perfect strategic crime for increased tension.<ref name=lavozdeasturias_190126 /><ref name=elcomercio_190808>{{cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-temporada-4-fecha-estreno-netflix-parte-4-trailer-historia-pasara-actores-personajes-money-heist-espana-ficha-tv-nnda-nnlt-noticia-650201 |title=\"La casa de papel\", temporada 4: fecha de estreno en Netflix, qu\u00e9 pasar\u00e1, actores, personajes, misterios y teor\u00edas |language=es |publisher=elcomercio.pe |date=10 August 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> Nearly all main characters, including the relationship-opposing Professor, eventually succumb to love,<ref name=elespectador_190718>{{cite web |last=Contreras Fajardo |first=Lilian |url=https://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/medios/la-casa-de-papel-3-robar-oro-para-recuperar-el-amor-articulo-871675 |title=\"La Casa de Papel 3\": robar oro para recuperar el amor |publisher=elespectador.com |language=es |date=18 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> for which the series received comparisons to [[telenovela]]s.<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /><ref name=theglobeandmail /> Comedic elements, which were compared to ''[[Back to the Future]]''<ref name=abc_170628>{{cite web |last=Soage |first=Noelia |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-entrevista-alvaro-morte-casa-papel-201706280112_noticia.html |title=\u00c1lvaro Morte: \"La casa de papel va a marcar un antes y un despu\u00e9s en la forma de tratar la ficci\u00f3n en este pa\u00eds\" |publisher=abc.es |language=es |date=28 June 2017 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> and [[black comedy]],<ref name=elpais_190614 /> also offset the heist tension.<ref name=variety_190801 /> The heist film formula is subverted by the heist starting straight after the opening credits instead of lingering on how the gang is brought together.<ref name=haaretz_180807>{{cite web |last=Hennigan |first=Adrian |url=https://www.haaretz.com/life/television/.premium-netflix-s-money-heist-will-steal-your-heart-and-your-weekend-1.5977887 |title=Netflix's 'Money Heist' Will Steal Your Heart and Your Weekend |publisher=[[haaretz.com]] |date=7 April 2018 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nWith the series being set after the [[financial crisis of 2007\u20132008]], which resulted in severe austerity measures in Spain,<ref name=theglobeandmail /> critics argued that the series was an explicit allegory of rebellion against capitalism,<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /><ref name=lemonde_190313>{{cite web |last=S\u00e9risier |first=Pierre |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/blog/seriestv/2018/03/13/la-casa-de-papel-allegorie-de-la-rebellion/ |title=La Casa de Papel \u2013 All\u00e9gorie de la r\u00e9bellion |language=fr |publisher=lemonde.fr |date=13 March 2018 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> including ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', who saw the series as \"subversive in that it's about a heist for the people. It's revenge against a government.\"<ref name=\"theglobeandmail\" /> According to ''[[Le Monde]]'', the Professor's teaching scenes in the Toledo hunting estate in particular highlighted how people should seek to develop their own solutions for the fallible capitalist system.<ref name=lemonde_190313 /> The show's [[Robin Hood]] analogy of robbing the rich and giving to the poor received various interpretations. ''[[El Espa\u00f1ol]]'' argued that the analogy made it easier for viewers to connect with the show, as modern society tended to be tired of banks and politics already,<ref name=elespanol_190724>{{cite web |last=Zurro |first=Javier |url=https://www.elespanol.com/cultura/series/20190724/netflix-no-tomes-pelo-casa-papel/415959462_0.html |title=Netflix, no nos tomes el pelo: 'La Casa de Papel' no es para tanto |language=es |publisher=elespanol.com|date=24 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> and ''The New Statesman'' said the rich were no longer stolen from but undermined at their roots.<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> On the other hand, [[Esquire (magazine)|''Esquire'']]'s Mireia Mullor saw the Robin Hood analogy as a mere distraction strategy for the robbers, as they initially did not plan to use the money from their first heist to improve the quality of life of regular people; for this reason, Mullor also argues that the large following for the robbers in part 3 was not comprehensible even though they represented a channel for the discontent of those bearing economic and political injustices.<ref name=esquire_190729>{{cite web |last=Mullor |first=Mireia |url=https://www.esquire.com/es/actualidad/tv/a28516581/la-casa-de-papel-temporada-3-critica-netflix/ |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019: Los pros y contras de la tercera temporada en Netflix |language=es |publisher=esquire.com |date=29 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe characters were designed as multi-dimensional and complementary [[antagonist]]s and [[anti-hero]]es whose moralities are ever-changing.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> Examples include Berlin, who shifts from a robber mistreating hostages, to one of the series' most beloved characters.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> There is also the hostage M\u00f3nica Gaztambide, as well as inspector Raquel Murillo, who eventually join the cause of the robbers.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> Gonz\u00e1lvez of ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' finds that an audience may think of the robbers as evil at first for committing a crime, but as the series progresses it marks the financial system as the true evil and suggests the robbers have ethical and empathetic justification for stealing from an overpowered thief.<ref name=huffingtonpost_190628>{{cite web |last=Gonz\u00e1lvez |first=Paula M. |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.es/entry/por-que-arrasa-la-casa-de-papel-en-todo-el-mundo-cada-detalle-esta-estudiado_es_5d14ff66e4b03d6116385913 |title=Qu\u00e9 ha hecho bien 'La Casa de Papel' para convertirse en la serie de habla no inglesa m\u00e1s vista de la historia de Netflix |language=es |publisher=huffingtonpost.es |date=28 June 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> Najwa Nimri, playing inspector Sierra in part 3, said that \"the complex thing about a villain is giving him humanity. That's where everyone gets alarmed, when you have to prove that a villain also has a heart\". She added that the amount of information and technology that surrounds us is allowing us to verify that \"everyone has a dark side.\"<ref name=huffingtonpost_190628 /> The series leaves it to the audience to decide who is good or bad, as characters are \"relatable and immoral\" at various points in the story.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> Pina argued that it was this ability to change view that made the series addictive and marked its success.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 />\n\nWith the relative number of female main characters in TV shows generally on the rise,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> the series gives female characters the same attention as men, which the [[BBC]] regarded as an innovation for Spanish television.<ref name=bbc_190312 /> While many plot lines in the heist series still relate to males,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> the female characters become increasingly aware of gender-related issues, such as M\u00f3nica arguing in part 3 that women, just like men, could be robbers and a good parent.<ref name=esquire_190722>{{cite web |last=Mart\u00edn |first=Cynthia |url=https://www.esquire.com/es/actualidad/a28443894/la-casa-de-papel-3-feminista-entrevista-alba-flores-darko-peric/ |title='La Casa de Papel 3' y su \"me too\" a la espa\u00f1ola |language=es |publisher=esquire.com |date=22 July 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Critics further examined [[feminist]] themes and a rejection of [[machismo]]<ref name=esquire_190722 /> in the series through Nairobi and her phrase \"The [[matriarchy]] begins\" in part 2,<ref name=publimetro_190719 /> and a comparative scene in part 3, where Palermo claims a [[patriarchy]] in a moment that, according to [[CNET]], is played for laughs.<ref name=cnet_190719>{{cite web |last=Puentes |first=Patricia |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/money-heist-3-netflix-review-bigger-heist-higher-stakes-same-red-coveralls/ |title=Money Heist 3 review: Bigger heist, higher stakes, same red coveralls |publisher=cnet.com |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=7 October 2019}}</ref> ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' challenged any female-empowering claims in the series, as \u00darsula Corber\u00f3 (Tokyo) was often shown scantily clad,<ref name=lavanguardia_190809>{{cite web |last=Sol\u00e0 Gimferrer |first=Pere |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/netflix/20190809/463948127016/la-casa-de-papel-tercera-parte-critica-presupuesto.html |title=Verdades inc\u00f3modas de series (I): La lecci\u00f3n de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |publisher=lavanguardia.com |date=9 August 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> and ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'' criticized how characters' relationship problems in part 3 were often portrayed to be the women's fault.<ref name=esquire_190729 /> Alba Flores (Nairobi) saw no inherent feminist plot in the series, as women only take control when it suits the story,<ref name=publimetro_190719>{{cite web |last=Cordovez |first=Karen |url=https://www.publimetro.cl/cl/entretenimiento/2019/07/19/nairobi-y-el-regreso-de-la-casa-de-papel-ahora-el-golpe-es-mas-ambicioso-porque-su-finalidad-es-mas-grande.html |title=\"Nairobi\" y el regreso de \"La Casa de Papel\": \"Ahora el golpe es m\u00e1s ambicioso porque su finalidad es m\u00e1s grande\" |language=es |publisher=publimetro.cl |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> whilst Esther Acebo (M\u00f3nica) described any feminist subtext in the show as not being vindictive.<ref name=huffingtonpost_190708>{{cite web |last=Gonz\u00e1lvez |first=Paula M. |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.es/entry/alvaro-morte-habia-un-rechazo-hacia-la-ficcion-espanola-por-el-mero-hecho-de-ser-espanola_es_5d14ec6be4b082e55365da00 |title=Najwa Nimri ('La Casa de Papel'): \"Tengo una experiencia clar\u00edsima con el \u00e9xito y si no te quieres exponer, no te expones\" |language=es |publisher=huffingtonpost.es |date=8 July 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n\n=== Original broadcast ===\n\n{{box\n| align = center\n|{{Television ratings graph\n<!--| title       = La Casa De Papel-->\n| country     = Antena 3\n| color1      = #A90712\n| color2      = #594022\n| average     = y\n| no_table = y\n| height = 200\n| bar_width   = 5\n| x_intervals = 5\n| y_intervals = 1\n| refs        = <ref>{{cite web |title=AUDIENCIAS LA CASA DE PAPEL |url=https://www.formulatv.com/series/la-casa-de-papel/audiencias/ |website=formulatv.com |accessdate=27 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180427032300/http://www.formulatv.com/series/la-casa-de-papel/audiencias/ |archivedate=27 April 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"La casa de papel\": La serie espa\u00f1ola que arrasa en el mundo |url=https://www.24horas.cl/tendencias/espectaculosycultura/la-casa-de-papel-la-serie-espanola-que-arrasa-en-el-mundo--2654256 |website=24horas.cl |accessdate=27 April 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| season_title = Part\n|-\n<!-- P01E01 -->| 4.090\n<!-- P01E02 -->| 3.041\n<!-- P01E03 -->| 2.646\n<!-- P01E04 -->| 2.655\n<!-- P01E05 -->| 2.366\n<!-- P01E06 -->| 2.474\n<!-- P01E07 -->| 2.420\n<!-- P01E08 -->| 2.070\n<!-- P01E09 -->| 2.196\n<!-- P01E10 -->| 1.995\n<!-- P01_AV -->| 2.595\n|-\n<!-- P02E11 -->| 1.737\n<!-- P02E12 -->| 1.571\n<!-- P02E13 -->| 1.539\n<!-- P02E14 -->| 1.487\n<!-- P02E15 -->| 1.80\n<!-- P02_AV -->| 1.627\n}}}}\n\nPart 1 aired on free-to-air Spanish TV channel [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] in the Wednesday 10:40&nbsp;p.m. time slot from 2 May 2017 till 27 June 2017.<ref name=elmundo_170502 /> Part 2 moved to the Monday 10:40&nbsp;p.m. time slot and was broadcast from 16 October 2017 till 23 November 2017,<ref name=elpais_171010>{{cite web |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2017/10/10/television/1507633357_409248.html |title=El atraco perfecto llega a su fin |website=elpais.com |language=es |date=15 October 2017 |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> with the originally planned 18-21 episodes cut down to 15.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /><ref name=eldario_170502>{{cite web |url=http://vertele.eldiario.es/noticias/entrevista-alex-pina-lacasadepapel-antena3_0_1897010292.html |title=\u00c1lex Pina presenta 'La casa de Papel': 'Vis a Vis fue un enorme banco de pruebas' |website=[[eldiario.es]] |language=es |date=2 May 2017 |access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref> As the series was developed with Spanish prime-time television in mind,<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> the episodes had a length of around 70 minutes, as is typical for Spanish television.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> The first five episodes of part 1 were followed by an [[aftershow]] entitled ''Tercer Grado'' ({{transl|es|IAST|Third Grade}}).<ref name=tercer_grado />\n\nDespite boycott calls after [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]] (Raquel Murillo) had protested against the accommodations of [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] prisoners of her home [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country]] in March 2016,<ref>{{cite web |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-itziar-ituno-piden-boicot-casa-papel-apoyo-protagonistas-otegui-y-presos-etarras-201705031050_noticia.html |title=Piden el boicot a \"La casa de papel\" por el apoyo de una de sus protagonistas a Otegui y al acercamiento de presos etarras |website=abc.es |language=es |date=4 May 2017 |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> the show had the best premiere of a Spanish series since April 2015,<ref name=larazon_170621/> with more than four million viewers and the majority share of viewers in its timeslot, almost double the number of the next highest-viewed station/show.<ref name=bbc_190312>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20190312-la-casa-de-papel-setting-the-bar-for-global-television |title=La Casa de Papel: Setting the bar for global television |last=Keishin Armstrong |first=Jennifer |website=[[bbc.com]] |access-date=10 August 2019 |date=13 March 2019}}</ref> The show received good reviews and remained a leader in the commercial target group for the first half of part 1,<ref name=larazon_170621>{{cite web |url=https://www.larazon.es/tv-y-comunicacion/tv-news/una-espectacular-explosion-y-plan-de-fuga-de-los-rehenes-en-la-casa-de-papel-AB15419339 |title=Una espectacular explosi\u00f3n y plan de fuga de los rehenes, en \u2018La casa de papel\u2019  |website=[[larazon.es]] |access-date=27 September 2019 |date=21 June 2017}}</ref> but the viewership eventually slipped to lower figures than expected by the Antena 3 executives.<ref name=elpais_171124 /> Argentine newspaper ''[[La Naci\u00f3n]]'' attributed the decrease in viewer numbers to the change in time slots, the late broadcast times and the summer break between the parts.<ref name=lanacion_190616 /> Pina saw the commercial breaks as responsible, as they disrupted the narrative flow of the series that otherwise played almost in real time, even though the breaks were factored in during writing.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' saw the interest only waning among the conventional audience, as the plot unfolded too slowly at the rate of one episode per week.<ref name=lavanguardia_190719 /> Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander regarded the series' run on Antena 3 as a \"failure\" in 2019, as the ratings declined to \"nothing special\", but commended Antena 3 for making a series that did not rely on typical stand-alone episodes.<ref name=elmundo_190912>{{cite web |last=D\u00edas-Guerra |first=I\u00f1ako |url=https://www.elmundo.es/papel/cultura/2019/09/12/5d791951fc6c8337538b45fe.html |title=Javier G\u00f3mez Santander: \"Los espa\u00f1oles no somos un buen ej\u00e9rcito, pero como guerrilla somos la hostia\" |website=elmundo.es |language=es |date=12 September 2019 |access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Netflix acquisition ===\n\nPart 1 was made available on [[Netflix|Netflix Spain]] on 1 July 2017, like other series belonging to Antena 3's parent media group [[Atresmedia]].<ref name=larazon_170630>{{Cite web |url=https://www.larazon.es/tv-y-comunicacion/tv-news/netflix-se-fija-de-nuevo-en-una-serie-de-atresmedia-compra-la-casa-de-papel-para-emitirla-en-todo-el-mundo-NJ15494977 |title=Netflix se fija, de nuevo, en una serie de Atresmedia: compra 'La casa de papel' para emitirla en todo el mundo |website=larazon.es |language=es |date=30 June 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> In December 2017, Netflix acquired the exclusive global streaming rights for the series.<ref name=bbc_190312 /><ref name=larazon_170630 /> Netflix re-cut the series into 22 episodes of around 50 minutes length.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Cliffhangers and scenes had to be divided and moved to other episodes, but this proved less drastic than expected because of the series' perpetual plot twists.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Netflix [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbed]] the series and renamed it from ''La casa de papel'' to ''Money Heist'' for distribution in the English-speaking world,<ref name=bbc_190312 /> releasing the first part on 20 December 2017 without any promotion.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /><ref name=elpais_lcdp /> The second part was made available for streaming on 6 April 2018.<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> Pina assessed the viewer experience on Antena 3 versus Netflix as \"very different\", although the essence of the series remained the same.<ref name=elpais_180326>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2018/03/26/television/1522083264_215034.html |title=Por qu\u00e9 \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 ha sido un inesperado \u00e9xito internacional |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=elpais.com |language=es |date=29 March 2018 |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box\n| title = \n| quote = \"[''Money Heist'' had] no promotion or anything. Netflix put it in that pile of series that it has, which is like the sock drawer that you never look in and from which only the algorithm can rescue you, and we didn't think it was a big deal.\"{{hidden begin}}\"Sin promoci\u00f3n ni nada. Netflix la meti\u00f3 en ese mont\u00f3n de series que tiene, que es como el caj\u00f3n de los calcetines que nunca miras y de donde s\u00f3lo te puede rescatar el algoritmo, y no le dimos ninguna importancia.\"{{hidden end}}\n| author = \u2014Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander\n| source = September 2019<ref name=elmundo_190912 />\n| align = right\n| width = 30%\n| bgcolor = lightblue\n}}\n\nWithout a dedicated Netflix marketing campaign,<ref name=elpais_180712 /> the series became the most-watched non-English language series on Netflix in early 2018, within four months of being added to the platform, to the creators' surprise.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s22.q4cdn.com/959853165/files/doc_financials/quarterly_reports/2018/q1/FINAL-Q1-18-Shareholder-Letter.pdf |title=Netflix Q1 2018 Letter to Shareholders |date=16 April 2018 |website=[[Netflix]] Investor Relations |pages=2\u20133 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626162529/https://ir.netflix.com/static-files/419958ac-5fd7-4bcd-9fb1-ebca445a9016 |archivedate=26 June 2018 |url-status=live |access-date=16 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> This prompted Netflix to sign a global exclusive overall deal with Pina shortly afterwards.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/netflix-global-exclusive-overall-deal-la-casa-de-papel-creator-alex-pina-1202871395/ |title=Netflix Signs Global Exclusive Overall Deal with \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 Creator Alex Pina |last=Hopewell |first=John |website=[[variety.com]] |access-date=11 August 2019 |date=12 July 2018}}</ref> Diego \u00c1valos, director of original content for Netflix in Europe, noted that the series was atypical in being watched across many different profile groups.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/08/01/television/1564671328_371797.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 logra m\u00e1s de 34 millones de espectadores y refuerza la estrategia internacional de Netflix |last=Avenda\u00f1o |first=Tom C. |website=elpais.com |language=es |access-date=27 September 2019 |date=2 August 2019}}</ref> Common explanations for the drastic differences in viewership between Antena 3 and Netflix were changed consumption habits of series viewers,<ref name=elpais_180326 /><ref name=elmundo_190912 /> and the [[binge-watching]] potential of streaming.<ref name=lavanguardia_190719 /><ref name=elpais_180326 /> Pina and Sonia Mart\u00ednez of Antena 3 would later say that the series, with its high demand of viewer attention, unknowingly followed the video-on-demand format from the beginning.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Meanwhile, people in Spain would discover the series on Netflix, unaware of its original Antena 3 broadcast.<ref name=elpais_180326 />\n\n=== Renewal ===\n\nIn October 2017, \u00c1lex Pina said that part 2 had remote but intentional spin-off possibilities, and that his team was open to continue the robbers' story in the form of movies or a Netflix renewal.<ref name=elconfidencial_171016>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-10-16/alex-pina-casa-papel-final-ministerio-tiempo-bertin-ursula-corbero_1459636/ |title=El creador de 'La casa de papel' se moja sobre su competencia: 'El Ministerio' y Bert\u00edn |language=es |date=16 October 2017 |website=elconfidencial.com |access-date=15 October 2019}}</ref> Following the show's success on the streaming platform, Netflix approached Pina and Atresmedia to produce new chapters for the originally self-contained story. The writers withdrew themselves for more than two months to decide on a direction,<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> creating a [[Bible (screenwriting)|bible]] with central ideas for new episodes in the process.<ref name=laprensa_190809 /> The crucial factors in accepting Netflix' deal were the creators recognising that characters still had things to say, and having the opportunity to deviate from the perfectly orchestrated heist of the first two parts.<ref name=elcomercio_190808 /> Adamant that the story should be set in Spain again,<ref name=elpais_190614 /> the producers wanted to make it a sequel rather than a direct continuation, and expand on the familiarity and affection between the characters instead of the former group of strangers.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> Rio's capture was chosen as the catalyst to get the gang back together, because he as the narrator's boyfriend represented the necessary emotional factor for the renewal not to be \"suicide\".<ref name=elcomercio_190720>{{Cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-temporada-3-trailer-fecha-estreno-sinopsis-personajes-tercera-parte-series-netflix-espana-money-heist-nnda-nnlt-noticia-556069 |title=\"La casa de papel\", temporada 3: fecha de estreno en Netflix, c\u00f3mo ver online, tr\u00e1iler, actores, personajes y cr\u00edtica |language=es |date=20 July 2019 |website=elcomercio.pe |access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nNetflix officially renewed the series for a third part with a considerably increased budget on 18 April 2018,<ref name=elperiodico_190627 /> which might make part 3 the most expensive series per episode in Spanish television history, according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref name=partiv/> As writing was in progress, Pina stated in July 2018 that he appreciated Netflix' decision to make the episodes 45 to 50 minutes of length, as the narrative could be more compressed and international viewers would have more freedom to consume the story in smaller parts.<ref name=elpais_180712 /> With Netflix' new push to improve the quality and appeal of its English-language versions of foreign shows, and over 70 percent of viewers in the United States choosing dubs over subtitles for the series, Netflix hired a new dubbing crew for part 3 and re-dubbed the first two parts accordingly.<ref name=\"nytimes_190719\">{{cite web |first=Jill |last=Goldsmith |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/19/arts/television/netflix-money-heist.html |title=Netflix Wants to Make Its Dubbed Foreign Shows Less Dubby |publisher=[[nytimes.com]] |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref> Part 3, consisting of eight episodes, was released on 19 July 2019;<ref name=\"elcomercio_190808\" /> the first two episodes of part 3 also had a limited theatrical release in Spain one day before.<ref name=\"partiv\" />\n\nIn August 2019, Netflix announced that part 3 was streamed by 34 million household accounts within its first week of release, of which 24 million finished the series within this period,<ref name=variety_190801>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/global/netflix-la-casa-de-papel-money-heist-part-3-smashes-records-1203288791/ |title=Netflix\u2019s \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 \u2013 \u2018Money Heist\u2019 \u2013 Part 3 Smashes Records |last2=Hopewell |first2=John |last=Lang |first=Jamie |work=variety.com |access-date=1 August 2019 |date=1 August 2019}}</ref> thereby making it one of the most-watched productions on Netflix of all time, regardless of language.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/08/02/money-heist-3-smashes-netflix-records-34million-tune-new-episodes-10506673/ |title=Money Heist smashes records as season 3 becomes Netflix's most watched show ever |publisher=metro.co.uk |last=Pierce |first=Tilly |date=2 August 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> Netflix had an estimated 148 million subscribers world-wide in mid-2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/netflix-la-casa-de-papel-part-3-wows-madrid-world-premiere-1203265758/ |title=Netflix\u2019s \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 Part 3 Wows at World Premiere |publisher=variety.com |last=Hopewell |first=John |date=12 July 2019 |access-date=2 October 2019}}</ref> In October 2019, Netflix ranked ''Money Heist'' as their third most-watched TV series for the past twelve months,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/17/business/media/netflix-top-ten-movies-tv-shows.html |title=Netflix\u2019s Top 10 Original Movies and TV Shows, According to Netflix |publisher=nytimes.com |last=Koblin |first=John |date=17 October 2019 |access-date=21 October 2019}}</ref> and named it as the most-watched series across several European markets in 2019, including France, Spain and Italy, though not the UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/la-casa-de-papel-money-heist-tops-netflix-charts-europe-1203453375/ |title=\u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 (\u2018Money Heist\u2019) Tops Netflix\u2019s Charts in Key European Markets |last=Keslassy |first=Elsa |work=variety.com |access-date=1 January 2020 |date=30 December 2019}}</ref> Twitter ranked the show fourth in its \"Top TV shows worldwide\" of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://blog.twitter.com/en_us/topics/insights/2019/ThisHappened-in-2019.html |title=#ThisHappened in 2019 |publisher=blog.twitter.com |last=Filadelfo |first=Elaine |date=9 December 2019 |access-date=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Future ===\n\nFilming of an initially unannounced fourth part ended in August 2019.<ref name=p4filmend>{{cite web |url=https://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/el-profesor-desmiente-su-salida-de-la-casa-de-papel-articulo-880949 |title=El Profesor desmiente su salida de La casa de papel |website=[[elespectador.com]] |date=13 September 2019 |access-date=1 October 2019}}</ref> It will consist of eight episodes.<ref name=\"elcomercio_190808\" /> Netflix announced in December 2019 that part 4 would be released on 3 April 2020;<ref name=netflix_191208>{{cite web |title=\u2018Money Heist\u2019 Season 4 Coming to Netflix in April 2020 |url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/news/money-heist-season-4-renewed-at-netflix-what-we-know-so-far-12-2019/ |website=What's on Netflix |date=December 8, 2019}}</ref> a documentary involving the producers and the cast will premiere on Netflix the same day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Netflix emitir\u00e1 un documental sobre el fen\u00f3meno de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |url=https://www.fotogramas.es/noticias-cine/a30713079/la-casa-de-papel-documental-netflix/ |author=Silvestre, Juan |website=fotogramas.es |date=30 January 2020 |access-date=30 January 2020 |language=es}}</ref> A trailer first shown during the [[Comic Con Experience]] (CCXP) in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] showed the gang members with and without masks, with Nairobi appearing last,<ref name=elpais_191209 /> indicating she would appear in part 4 and resulting in her name becoming a Trending Topic online, ahead of the series itself.<ref name=eldiario_191209 /> Also at CCXP, a scene from the beginning of part 4 was shown, in which the Professor, still in the woods, flees from the police, jumps over a wall to hide and encounters a menacing bull.<ref name=elpais_191209 /><ref name=eldiario_191209>{{cite web |title=Primera escena de 'La casa de papel 4' y Trending Topic para Nairobi |url=http://vertele.eldiario.es/noticias/La-casa-de-papel-Parte-4-Primera-escena-Nairobi_0_2184381549.html |website=vertele.eldiario.es |date=December 9, 2019 |access-date=9 December 2019 |language=es}}</ref> \u00c1lex Pina and writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander stated that unlike part 3, where the intention was to re-attract the audience with high-energy drama after the move to Netflix, the story of part 4 would unfold slower and be more character-driven.<ref>{{cite web |title=Creadores de La Casa de Papel nos cuentan c\u00f3mo ser\u00e1 la cuarta temporada |url=https://www.estilodf.tv/lo-mas-destacado/creadores-de-la-casa-de-papel-nos-cuentan-como-sera-la-cuarta-temporada |author=Ortiz, Paola |website=estilodf.tv |date=October 4, 2019 |access-date=10 December 2019 |language=es}}</ref> At another occasion, Pina and executive producer Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato teased part 4 as the \"most traumatic [part] of all\" because \"this much tension has to explode somewhere\".<ref name=abc_191215 /> Alba Flores (Nairobi) said the scriptwriters had previously made many concessions to fans in part 3, but would go against audience wishes in part 4 and that \"anyone who loves Nairobi will suffer\".<ref name=elpais_191209 /> According to Pedro Alonso (Berlin), the focus of part 4 will be on saving Nairobi's life and standing by each other to survive.<ref name=elpais_191209>{{cite web |title=\u201cQuien quiera a Nairobi va a sufrir\u201d: El elenco de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 promete sorpresas en la nueva temporada |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/12/09/television/1575911603_998928.html/ |author=Oliveira, Joana |website=elpais.com |date=10 December 2019 |access-date=10 December 2019 |language=es}}</ref>\n\nIt\u2019s taken a while for it to get discovered in the past times by people at large, but now it\u2019s totally different: The Spanish language series La Casa De Papel or Money Heist is finally being recognized as one of the most intriguing entertainings binge-watches in recent times.\n\nThe series is like Ocean\u2019s 11 but with eight robbers who enter the Royal Mint of Spain in broad daylight to carry out the biggest heist of all time, except Danny Ocean, or the Professor is Bossman handling the mission and police negotiations from the outside. Though there is no Brad Pitt here, the Sexy Ursula Corbero more than makes up for it.\n\nMoney Heist is finally coming back with Part 4 (or sometimes also referred to as Season 4). In just under a month releasing globally on Netflix on April 3rd, 2020. The explosive Spanish Series is among the most popular titles on Netflix. [https://www.worldtamilrockers.com/money-heist-part-4-netflix-release-date-cast-spoilers/ World Tamil Rockers]\n\nIn October 2019, the online editions of Spanish newspapers ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' and ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' re-reported claims by the Spanish website {{Interlanguage link|formulatv.com|es|F\u00f3rmula TV}} that Netflix had renewed the series for a fifth part, and that pre-production had already begun.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/cultura/abci-casa-papel-tendra-5-temporada-netflix-201910141657_video.html |title=La casa de papel tendr\u00e1 5\u00aa temporada en Netflix |language=es |date=14 October 2019 |website=abc.es |access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/netflix/20191015/47996801852/la-casa-de-papel-netflix-temporada-5.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019, renovada por una quinta temporada en Netflix |language=es |date=15 October 2019 |website=lavanguardia.com |access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.formulatv.com/noticias/netflix-renueva-la-casa-de-papel-quinta-temporada-alvaro-morte-96344/ |title=Netflix renueva 'La Casa de Papel' por una quinta temporada que volver\u00e1 a contar con \u00c1lvaro Morte |language=es |date=14 October 2019 |website=formulatv.com |access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, ''La Vanguardia'' quoted director Jes\u00fas Colmenar's statement \"That there is going to be a fifth [part] can be said\", and that the new part would be filmed after Vancouver Media's new project ''[[Sky Rojo]]''.<ref name=lavanguardia_191117>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/local/sevilla/20191117/471696494420/director-de-la-casa-de-papel-la-cuarta-temporada-va-a-ser-mas-dura-para-el-espectador.html |title=Director de 'La Casa de Papel': \"La cuarta temporada va a ser m\u00e1s dura para el espectador\" |language=es |date=17 November 2019 |website=lavanguardia.com |access-date=17 November 2019 |quote=[Colmenar ha precisado que ''[[Sky Rojo]]''] se producir\u00e1 entre la cuarta y la quinta temporada de ''La Casa de Papel''. \"Que hay quinta temporada s\u00ed se puede decir\", ha concluido entre risas tras ser advertido por [[Pedro Alonso]].}}</ref> Colmenar also stated that there have been discussions with Netflix about creating a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of the series.<ref name=lavanguardia_191117 /> In an interview in December 2019, Pina and Mart\u00ednez Lobato would not discuss the possibility of a fifth part because of confidentiality contracts, and only said that \"Someone knows there will be [a part 5], but we don't.\"<ref name=abc_191215>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-alex-pina-creador-casa-papel-somos-unos-perturbados-autocritica-201912150042_noticia.html |title=\u00c1lex Pina, creador de \u00abLa casa de papel\u00bb: \u00abSomos unos perturbados de la autocr\u00edtica\u00bb |last=Cort\u00e9s |first=Helena |language=es |date=15 December 2019 |website=abc.es |access-date=15 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Public response ===\n\n[[File:Casa_de_Papel_at_Patras_Carnival_(cropped).jpg|thumb|right|240px|[[Cosplay]] in [[Patras]], Greece, in 2019.]]\n\nAfter the move to Netflix, the series remained the most-followed series on Netflix for six consecutive weeks and became one of the most popular series on [[IMDb]].<ref name=elpais_180326 /> It regularly trended on [[Twitter]] world-wide, largely because celebrities commented on it, such as football players [[Neymar]] and [[Marc Bartra]], American singer [[Romeo Santos]],<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> and author [[Stephen King]].<ref name=cnet_190719 /> While users flooded social networks with media of themselves wearing the robbers' outfit,<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> the robbers' costumes were worn at the [[Rio Carnival]], and Dal\u00ed icons were shown on huge banners in [[Saudi Arabia]] football stadiums.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Real footage of these events would later be shown in part 3 as a tribute to the show's international success.<ref name=abc_190725>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/criticas/abci-casa-papel-3-critica-tercera-temporada-casa-papel-asalto-golpe-billete-nunca-mejor-dicho-201907250839_noticia.html |title=Cr\u00edtica de la tercera temporada de \"La casa de papel\": Asalto a golpe de billete... nunca mejor dicho |last=Jim\u00e9nez |first=Alex |website=abc.es |access-date=28 September 2019 |date=25 June 2019 |language=es}}</ref> The [[Mus\u00e9e Gr\u00e9vin]] in [[Paris]] added statues of the robbers to its wax museum in summer 2018.<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> The show's iconography was used prominently by third parties for advertising,<ref>{{cite AV media |date=24 September 2019 |title=Santa Isabel - La Casa del Ahorro |language=es |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oQAOSJB8ISk |access-date=4 October 2019 |publisher=[[Santa Isabel (supermarkets)|Santa Isabel]] via youtube.com}}</ref> sports presentations,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.am.com.mx/superdeportivo/Robaran-la-Liga-Tlaxcala-FC-presenta-nueva-camiseta-a-La-Casa-de-Papel-20190809-0050.html |title=\u00bfRobar\u00e1n la Liga? Tlaxcala FC presenta nueva camiseta a 'La Casa de Papel' |last=Jim\u00e9nez |first=Alex |website=am.com.mx |access-date=28 September 2019 |date=9 August 2019 |language=es}}</ref> and in porn.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-xvideos-llega-casa-raquel-version-porno-casa-papel-201909271203_noticia.html |title=Llega \"La casa de Raquel\", la versi\u00f3n porno de \"La casa de papel\" |last=Jim\u00e9nez |access-date=4 October 2019 |date=27 September 2019 |language=es}}</ref>\n\nThere have also been negative responses to the influence of the show. In numerous incidents, real heist men wore the show's red costumes and Dal\u00ec masks in their attacks or copied the fictional robbers' infiltration plans.<ref name=newstatesman_180824>{{cite web |url=https://www.newstatesman.com/culture/tv-radio/2018/08/spanish-hit-series-la-casa-de-papel-captures-europe-s-mood-decade-after |title=Spanish hit series \"La Casa de Papel\" captures Europe\u2019s mood a decade after the crash |last=Bock |first=Pauline |website=newstatesman.com |access-date=11 August 2019 |date=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref name=elpais_lcdp /><ref name=abc_190807>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-efecto-toxico-casa-papel-201908071042_noticia.html |title=El efecto \"t\u00f3xico\" de \"La casa de papel\"  |last=Zamora |first=I. |website=abc.es |access-date=4 October 2019 |date=7 August 2019 |language=es}}</ref> The robbers' costumes were banned at the 2019 [[Limassol Carnival Festival]] as a security measure as a result.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.euronews.com/2018/11/14/cypriot-carnival-bans-costumes-inspired-by-netflix-series-money-heist |title=Cypriot carnival bans costumes inspired by Netflix series 'Money Heist' |last=Rodriguez Martinez |first=Marta |website=euronews.com |access-date=4 October 2019 |date=14 November 2018 |language=es}}</ref> The series was used in an attack on [[YouTube]], when hackers removed the most-played song in the platform's history, \"[[Despacito]]\", and left an image of the show instead.<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> In unrelated reports, a journalist from the Turkish state channel AkitTV and an Ankaran politician have both warned against the show for supposedly encouraging terrorism and being \"a dangerous symbol of rebellion\".<ref name=newstatesman_180824 />\n\nSpanish newspaper ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'' saw the public response as a reflection of the \"climate of global disenchantment\" where the robbers represent the \"perfect antiheroes\",<ref name=elmundo_190719 /> and ''[[The New Statesman]]'' explained the show's resonance with international audiences as coming from the \"social and economic tensions it depicts, and because of the utopian escape it offers\".<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> Viewer response was especially high in Mediterranean Europe and the Latin world, in particular Spain, [[Italy]], [[France]], [[Portugal]], [[Brazil]], [[Chile]] and [[Argentina]],<ref name=elcomercio_190808 /> so Spanish as a common language did not appear to be a unifying reason for the show's success.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander and actor Pedro Alonso (Berlin) rather argued that the Latin world used to feel at the periphery of global importance, but a new sentiment was coming that Spain could compete with the global players in terms of media production levels and give the rest of the world a voice.<ref name=variety_190801 /><ref name=elmundo_190912 />\n\n=== Critical reception ===\n\nThe series' beginning on Antena 3 was received well by Spanish media.<ref name=larazon_170621 /> Nay\u00edn Costas of ''[[El Confidencial]]'' named the premiere a promising start that captivated viewers with \"adrenaline, well-dosed touches of humor and a lot of tension\", but considered it a challenge to maintain the dramatic tension for the remainder of the series.<ref>{{cite web |last=Costas |first=Nay\u00edn |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-05-02/critica-la-casa-de-papel-serie-antena3-ursula-corbero-alba-flores_1375703/ |title='La casa de papel' sube el list\u00f3n con un impecable, y cinematogr\u00e1fico, piloto |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=2 May 2017 |access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref> While considering the pilot's voice-over narration unnecessary and the sound editing and dialogs lacking, Natalia Marcos of ''[[El Pa\u00eds]]'' enjoyed the show's ensemble cast and the ambition, saying \"It is daring, brazen and entertaining, at least when it starts. Now we want more, which is not little.\"<ref name=elpais_170503 /> Reviewing the full first part, Marcos lauded the series for its outstanding direction, musical selection and for trying to innovate Spanish television, but criticized the length and ebbing tension.<ref name=elpais_171124>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2017/11/24/television/1511480525_162365.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 ha ganado |language=es |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=[[elpais.com]] |access-date=12 August 2019 |date=24 November 2017}}</ref> At the end of the series' original run, Nay\u00edn Costas of ''El Confidencial'' commended the series for its \"high quality closure\" that may make the finale \"one of the best episodes of the Spanish season\", but regretted that it aimed to satisfy viewers with a predictable happy ending rather than risk to \"do something different, original, ambitious\", and that the show was unable to follow in the footsteps of Pina's ''[[Locked Up (TV series)|Locked Up]]''.<ref name=elconfidencial_171123>{{cite web |last=Costas |first=Nay\u00edn |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-11-23/final-como-acaba-la-casa-de-papel-muerte-berlin-hermano-profesor_1482592/ |title=Final feliz en 'La casa de papel', un gran cap\u00edtulo lastrado por la falta de sorpresa |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=23 November 2017 |access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter the show's move to Netflix for its international release, Adrian Hennigan of the Israeli ''[[Haaretz]]'' said the series was \"more of a twisty thriller than soapy telenovela, driven by its ingenious plot, engaging characters, tense flash points, pulsating score and occasional moments of humor\", but taunted the English title \"Money Heist\" as bland.<ref name=haaretz_180807 /> In a scathing review, Pauline Bock of the British magazine ''[[New Statesman]]'' questioned the global hype of the series, saying that it was \"full of plot holes, clich\u00e9d slow-motions, corny love stories and gratuitous sex scenes\", before continuing to add that \"the music is pompous, the voice-over irritating, and it's terribly edited\".<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> [[John Doyle (critic)|John Doyle]] of ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' praised parts 1 and 2 for the heist genre subversions; he also said that the series could be \"deliciously melodramatic at times\" with \"outrageous twists and much passion\" like a telenovela.<ref name=theglobeandmail>{{cite web |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-three-great-foreign-dramas-on-netflix-for-a-summer-binge/?cmpid=rss1 |title=Three great foreign dramas on Netflix for a summer binge |last=Doyle |first=John |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |access-date=12 August 2019 |date=22 June 2018}}</ref> Jennifer Keishin Armstrong of the [[BBC]] saw the series' true appeal in the interpersonal dramas emerging through the heist between \"the beautiful robbers, their beautiful hostages and the beautiful authorities trying to negotiate with them.\"<ref name=bbc_190312 /> David Hugendick of ''[[Die Zeit]]'' found the series \"sometimes a bit sentimental, a little cartoonesque\", and the drama sometimes too telenovela-like, but \"all with a good sense for timing and spectacle.\"<ref name=zeit_180410>{{cite web |last=Hugendick |first=David |url=https://www.zeit.de/kultur/film/2018-04/haus-des-geldes-serie-netflix |title=Knackt das System! |language=de |publisher=[[zeit.de]] |date=10 April 2018 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] gave part 3 an approval rating of 100% based on 11 reviews, with an average rating of 7/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"An audacious plan told in a non-linear fashion keeps the third installment moving as ''Money Heist'' refocuses on the relations between its beloved characters.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/la_casa_de_papel/s03 |title=Money Heist: Part 3 (2019) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=18 October 2019}}</ref> While lauding the technical achievements, Javier Zurro of ''[[El Espa\u00f1ol]]'' described the third part as \"first-class entertainment\" that was unable to transcend its roots and lacked novelty. He felt unaffected by the internal drama between the characters and specifically disliked Tokyo's narration for its hollowness.<ref name=elespanol_190724 /> Alex Jim\u00e9nez of Spanish newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' found part 3 mostly succeeding in its attempts to reinvent the show and stay fresh.<ref name=abc_190725 />  Euan Ferguson of ''[[The Guardian]]'' recommended watching part 3, as \"it's still a glorious ''[[Peaky Blinders (TV series)|Peaky Blinders]]'', just with [[tapas]] and subtitles\",<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2019/jul/28/week-in-tv-i-am-nicola-orange-is-new-black-keeping-faith-money-heist |title=The week in TV: I Am Nicola; Orange Is the New Black; Keeping Faith; Money Heist |last=Ferguson |first=Euan |publisher=theguardian.com |access-date=7 October 2019 |date=28 July 2019}}</ref> while Pere Sol\u00e0 Gimferrer of ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' found that the amount of plot holes in part 3 could only be endured with constant [[suspension of disbelief]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190809 /> Though entertained, Alfonso Rivadeneyra Garc\u00eda of Peruvian newspaper ''[[El Comercio (Peru)|El Comercio]]'' said the show does \"what it does best: pretend to be the smartest boy in class when, in fact, it is only the most alive.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-temporada-3-review-resena-spoilers-netflix-ecpm-noticia-654511 |title=\"La casa de papel\" temporada 3: rese\u00f1amos sin SPOILERS los primeros 3 episodios |language=es |last=Rivadeneyra Garc\u00eda |first=Alfonso |publisher=elcomercio.pe |access-date=3 October 2019 |date=19 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards and nominations ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:95%; width:99%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! style=\"width:30%;\" | Category\n! style=\"width:40%;\" | Nominee(s)\n! Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2017\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Premios Feroz]]\n| Best drama series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cita web|title=La lista completa de ganadores de los premios Feroz 2018|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.es/2018/01/22/la-lista-completa-de-ganadores-de-los-premios-feroz-2018_a_23339879/|date=22 January 2018|publisher=huffingtonpost.es|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best leading actress of a series\n| [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best supporting actor in a series\n| [[Paco Tous]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best supporting actress in a series\n| [[Alba Flores]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 19th {{Interlanguage link|Premios IRIS|es|Premios Iris (Espa\u00f1a)}}\n| Best screenplay\n| [[\u00c1lex Pina]], Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato, David Barrocal, Pablo Roa, Esther Morales, Fernando Sancrist\u00f3bal, Javier G\u00f3mez Santander\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web |title=XIX Premios Iris |url=https://www.academiatv.es/premios/iris-2017/ |access-date=26 October 2019 |website=academiatv.es |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[FesTVal|FesTVal de Televisi\u00f3n y Radios de Vitoria]] \n| Best direction in fiction\n| Jes\u00fas Colmenar, Alejandro Bazzano, Miguel \u00c1ngel Vivas, \u00c1lex Rodrigo\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cita web |url=http://www.festval.tv/amplia/34963/galardones-2017.html |title=FesTVal Vitoria \u00b7 Festival de la Televisi\u00f3n |access-date=16 December 2017 |website=festval.tv |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best fiction (by critics)\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | {{Interlanguage link|68th Fotogramas de Plata|es|Anexo:Fotogramas de Plata 2017}}\n| Best Spanish series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web |title='La casa de papel', mejor serie espa\u00f1ola seg\u00fan los lectores |url=https://www.fotogramas.es/fotogramas-de-plata/a19459528/la-casa-de-papel-mejor-serie-espanola-segun-los-lectores/ |date=25 February 2018 |access-date=26 October 2019 |website=fotogramas.es |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"12\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[46th International Emmy Awards]]\n| Best drama series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/international-emmy-awards-winners-list-nevsu-money-heist-man-in-an-orange-shirt-1202505247/ |title='International Emmy Awards: \u2018Money Heist\u2019, \u2018Nevsu\u2019 Among Honorees \u2013 Complete Winners List |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=20 November 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=20 November 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 20th {{Interlanguage link|Premios IRIS|es|Premios Iris (Espa\u00f1a)}}\n| Best actress\n| [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=XX Premios Iris |url=https://www.academiatv.es/premios/iris-2018/ |publisher=academiatv.es |accessdate=26 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | Premios MiM Series \n| Best direction\n| Jes\u00fas Colmenar, Alejandro Bazzano, Miguel \u00c1ngel Vivas, \u00c1lex Rodrigo\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=larazon_180620>{{cite web |url=https://www.larazon.es/tv-y-comunicacion/tv-news/la-casa-de-papel-gana-el-premio-a-mejor-serie-dramatica-en-el-festival-de-montecarlo-EJ18774671 |title=\u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 gana el premio a Mejor Serie Dram\u00e1tica en el Festival de Montecarlo |website=La Raz\u00f3n |date=20 June 2018 |access-date=16 September 2018 |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Golden Nymph]]\n| Best drama TV series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=larazon_180620 />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | Premios de la {{Interlanguage link|Uni\u00f3n de Actores|es|Uni\u00f3n de Actores y Actrices}}\n| Best supporting television actor\n| [[Pedro Alonso]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cita web |url=https://www.culturaenserie.com/los-actores-la-casa-papel-las-principales-nominaciones-los-premios-la-union-actores.html |title=Los actores de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 se llevan la mayor\u00eda de las nominaciones de los Premios de la Uni\u00f3n de actores |date=13 February 2018 |access-date=16 September 2018 |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best supporting television actress\n| [[Alba Flores]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best television actor\n| [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best TV cast actor\n| [[Jaime Lorente]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best stand-out actress\n| [[Esther Acebo]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | {{Interlanguage link|Premios F\u00e9nix|es}}\n| Best series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/yotele/20181108/nuevo-reconocimiento-internacional-casa-papel-mejor-serie-premios-fenix-7137011 |title=Nuevo reconocimiento internacional para 'La Casa de Papel': Mejor Serie en los Premios F\u00e9nix |publisher=elperiodico.com |date=8 November 2018 |access-date=12 November 2018 |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{Interlanguage link|Festival de Luchon|fr|Festival des cr\u00e9ations t\u00e9l\u00e9visuelles de Luchon}}\n| Audience Choice Award\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://vancouvermedia.es/en/la-casa-de-papel-doblemente-premiada-en-el-festival-de-luchon/ |title=La casa de papel - Money Heist: Double Award At Festival de Luchon |publisher=vancouvermedia.es |access-date=26 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Jury Spanish Series Award\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2019\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 21st {{Interlanguage link|Premios IRIS|es|Premios Iris (Espa\u00f1a)}}\n| Best actor\n| [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]\n| {{win}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title='La casa de papel' arrasa con cinco galardones en los Premios Iris |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2019/11/19/5dd3319c21efa088798b4717.html |publisher=elmundo.es |date=19 November 2019 |accessdate=19 November 2019 |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best actress\n| [[Alba Flores]] \n| {{win}}\n|-\n| Best direction\n| Jes\u00fas Colmenar, \u00c1lex Rodrigo, Koldo Serra, Javier Quintas\n| {{win}}\n|-\n| Best fiction\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{win}}\n|-\n| Best production\n| Cristina L\u00f3pez Ferrar\n| {{win}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2020\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Premios Feroz]]\n| Best drama series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cita web |title=As\u00ed quedan las nominaciones a los Premios Feroz |url=https://www.fotogramas.es/noticias-cine/a30052596/premios-feroz-nominaciones-2020/ |author=Aller, Mar\u00eda |date=29 November 2019 |publisher=fotogramas.es |accessdate=6 December 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best leading actor of a series\n| [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best supporting actress in a series\n| [[Alba Flores]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=tercer_grado>{{cite AV media |title=Tercer Grado |language=es |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/tercer-grado/ |access-date=13 September 2019 |publisher=antena3.com}} {{bulleted list\n| For the casting of M\u00f3nica and Arturo, see {{cite AV media |date=9 May 2017<!--air date--> |title=Tercer Grado 2: Accedemos en exclusiva a los castings de Enrique Arce y Esther Acebo en \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/tercer-grado/accedemos-en-exclusiva-a-los-castings-de-enrique-arce-y-esther-acebo-en-la-casa-de-papel_201705105912b53d0cf2a1da48263fcb.html}} \n| For the casting of Helsinki and Denver, see {{cite AV media |date=16 May 2017<!--air date--> |title=Tercer Grado 3: Yolanda Serrano: \"Denver existi\u00f3 en cuanto Jaime Lorente hizo el papel en el casting\" |language=es |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/tercer-grado/denver-existio-en-cuanto-lo-hizo-el_20170517591c0edb0cf285e33517f49b.html}} \n| For the casting of Tokyo and Rio, see {{cite AV media |date=25 May 2017<!--air date--> |title=Tercer Grado 4: \u00darsula Corber\u00f3 y Miguel Herr\u00e1n se enfrentan a sus pruebas de casting |language=es |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/tercer-grado/ursula-corbero-y-miguel-herran-se-enfrentan-a-sus-pruebas-de-casting_201705255927a8960cf205e8f70050df.html}} \n| For the casting of the Professor and Nairobi, see {{cite AV media |date=1 June 2017<!--air date--> |title=Tercer Grado 5: El casting de El Profesor: \"\u00c1lvaro hace que quieras al personaje\" |language=es |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/tercer-grado/el-casting-de-el-profesor-alvaro-hace-que-quieras-al-personaje_201706015930e3190cf263918453e3d1.html}}}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.netflix.com/title/80192098}}\n* {{IMDb title|6468322}}\n\n{{Netflix original continuation series}}\n{{InternationalEmmyAward DramaSeries}}\n\n[[Category:2010s crime drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Spanish television series]]\n[[Category:2017 Spanish television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Antena 3 (Spain) network series]]\n[[Category:Crime thriller television series]]\n[[Category:Spanish crime television series]]\n[[Category:Spanish drama television series]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Madrid]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Panama]]\n[[Category:International Emmy Award for Best Drama Series winners]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{good article}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Money Heist\n| image                    = La casa de papel intertitle.png\n| caption                  = \n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|es|La casa de papel}} \n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Crime drama]]<ref name=nytimes_190719 />\n* [[Heist film|Heist]]<ref name=haaretz_180807 />\n* [[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]<ref name=antenacast />\n}}\n| creator                  = [[\u00c1lex Pina]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n<!-- Main and recurring are split and ordered as they appear in the series' credits. -->\n* [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]\n* [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]]\n* [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]\n* [[Paco Tous]]\n* [[Pedro Alonso]]\n* [[Alba Flores]]\n* [[Miguel Herr\u00e1n]]\n* [[Jaime Lorente]]\n* [[Esther Acebo]]\n* [[Enrique Arce]]\n* [[Mar\u00eda Pedraza]]\n* [[Darko Peri\u0107 (actor)|Darko Peri\u0107]]\n* [[Kiti M\u00e1nver]]\n* Hovik Keuchkerian\n* [[Rodrigo de la Serna]]\n* [[Najwa Nimri]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Manel Santisteban\n| opentheme                = \"My Life Is Going On\" by Cecilia Krull\n| composer                 = {{Plainlist|\n* Manel Santisteban\n* Iv\u00e1n Mart\u00ednez Lac\u00e1mara\n}}\n| country                  = Spain\n| language                 = Spanish\n| num_seasons              = <!-- READ: It is TWO seasons, but THREE aired parts as of August 2019.-->2 (3 parts){{efn|name=SeasonPart}}\n| num_episodes             = <!-- READ: The original release saw 15 episodes aired. Do not change this entry to the 30, which include the Netflix re-edited 22 episodes from part 1 and 2. -->23\n| list_episodes            = List of Money Heist episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* \u00c1lex Pina\n* Sonia Mart\u00ednez\n* Jes\u00fas Colmenar\n* Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato\n* Nacho Manubens\n}}\n| location                 = Madrid\n| cinematography           = Migue Amoedo\n| editor                   = {{Plainlist|\n* David Pelegr\u00edn\n* Luis Miguel Gonz\u00e1lez Bedmar\n* Ver\u00f3nica Call\u00f3n\n* Ra\u00fal Mora\n* Regino Hern\u00e1ndez\n* Raquel Marraco\n* Patricia Rubio\n}}\n| camera                   = Single-camera\n| runtime                  = 67\u201377 minutes (Antena 3)<br>41\u201357 minutes (Netflix)\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Vancouver Media\n* [[Atresmedia]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Netflix]]\n| picture_format           = {{Plainlist|\n1080p (16:9 HDTV)\n* 4K (16:9 UHDTV)\n}}\n| audio_format             = 5.1 surround sound\n| channel                  = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] (2017)\n* [[Netflix]] (2019)<!-- Netflix is the original network for part 3 in 2019. The first two parts in 2017 had Antena 3 as original network. -->\n}}\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2017|5|2|df=yes}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = https://www.netflix.com/title/80192098\n}}\n\n'''''Money Heist''''' ({{lang-es|'''La casa de papel'''}}, {{trans|The House of Paper}}) is a Spanish television [[heist genre|heist]] [[crime drama]] series. Created by [[\u00c1lex Pina]], the series was initially intended as a limited series to be told in two parts. It had its original run of 15 episodes on Spanish network [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] from 2 May 2017 through 23 November 2017. [[Netflix]] acquired the global streaming rights in late 2017. It re-cut the series into 22 shorter episodes and released them worldwide, beginning with the first part on 20 December 2017, followed by the second part on 6 April 2018. In April 2018, Netflix renewed the series with a significantly increased budget for 16 new episodes total. Part 3, with eight episodes, was released on 19 July 2019. Part 4, also with eight episodes, will be released on 3 April 2020. A documentary involving the producers and the cast will premiere on Netflix the same day, titled ''Money Heist: The Phenomenon''.\n\nThe first two parts revolve around a long-prepared, multi-day assault on the [[Royal Mint of Spain]] in [[Madrid]], in which a group of robbers take hostages as part of their plan to print and escape with \u20ac2.4 billion. It involves eight robbers, code-named after cities and led by the Professor ([[\u00c1lvaro Morte]]) from an external location. The story is primarily focused on one of the robbers, Tokyo ([[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]), as they battle with hostages on the inside and the police on the outside. In the third part, the surviving robbers are forced out of hiding, and with the help of new members, they plan and perform an assault on the [[Bank of Spain]].\n\nThe series was filmed in Madrid, Spain. Significant portions of part 3 were also filmed in [[Panama]], [[Thailand]] and [[Florence]], Italy. The narrative is told in a real-time-like fashion and relies on flashbacks, time-jumps, hidden character motivations and an unreliable narrator for complexity. The series subverts the heist genre by being told from the perspective of a woman (Tokyo) and having a strong [[Spaniard|Spanish]] identity, where emotional dynamics offset the perfect strategic crime.\n\nThe series received critical acclaim for its sophisticated plot, interpersonal dramas, direction and for trying to innovate Spanish television. The Italian anti-fascist song \"[[Bella ciao]]\", which plays multiple times throughout the series, became a summer hit across Europe in 2018. By 2018, the series was the most-watched non-English language series and one of the most-watched series overall on Netflix,<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> with a particular resonance coming from viewers from Mediterranean Europe and the Latin world.\n\n== Series overview ==\n{{main|List of Money Heist episodes}}\n{{:List of Money Heist episodes}}\n\n=== Season 1: Parts 1 and 2 (2017) ===\n\nPart 1 begins with the aftermath of a failed bank robbery by a woman named \"Tokyo\", as a man named the \"Professor\" saves her from being caught by the police and proposes her a heist of drastic proportions. After a brief outline of the planned heist, the story jumps to the beginning of a multi-day assault on the [[Royal Mint of Spain]] in [[Madrid]]. The eight robbers are code-named after cities: Tokyo, Moscow, Berlin, Nairobi, Rio, Denver, Helsinki and Oslo. Dressed in red jumpsuits with a mask of the Spanish painter [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]], the group of robbers take 67 hostages as part of their plan to print and escape with \u20ac2.4 billion through a self-built escape tunnel. The Professor heads the heist from an external location. Flashbacks throughout the series show the five months of preparation in an abandoned hunting estate in the [[Province of Toledo|Toledo]] countryside; the robbers are not to share personal information nor engage in personal relationships, and the assault shall be without bloodshed.\n\nThroughout parts 1 and 2, the robbers inside the Mint have difficulties sticking to the pre-defined rules, and face uncooperative hostages, violence, isolation, and mutiny. Tokyo commentates the events through [[voice-over]]s. While Denver pursues a love affair with the hostage M\u00f3nica Gaztambide, inspector Raquel Murillo of the [[National Police Corps]] negotiates with the Professor on the outside and begins an intimate relationship with his alter ego \"Salva\". The Professor's identity is repeatedly close to being uncovered, until Raquel realises his true identity, but is emotionally unable and unwilling to hand him over to the police. At the end of part 2, after 128 hours, the robbers escape successfully from the Mint with \u20ac984 million printed, but at the cost of the lives of Oslo, Moscow and Berlin. One year after the heist, Raquel decodes postcards left by the Professor for a location in [[Palawan]] in the Philippines, where she reunites with him.\n\n=== Season 2: Part 3 (2019) ===\n\nPart 3 begins two to three years after the heist on the Royal Mint of Spain, showing the robbers enjoying their lives paired-up in diverse locations. However, when [[Europol]] captures Rio with an intercepted phone, the Professor picks up Berlin's old plans to assault the [[Bank of Spain]] to force Europol to hand over Rio. He and Raquel (going by \"Lisbon\") get the gang, including M\u00f3nica (going by \"Stockholm\"), back together and enlist three new members: Bogot\u00e1, Palermo and Marseille. Flashbacks to the Professor and Berlin outline the planned new heist and their different approaches to love. The disguised robbers sneak into the heavily guarded bank, take hostages and eventually gain access to the gold and state secrets, while the Professor and Lisbon travel in an [[RV]] and then an ambulance while communicating with the robbers and the police. A breach in the bank is thwarted, forcing the police, led by Colonel Luis Tamayo and pregnant inspector Alicia Sierra, to release Rio to the robbers. Nairobi gets gravely injured by a police-inflicted [[sniper]] shot in the chest, and Lisbon is caught by the police. With another police assault on the bank incoming, and believing Lisbon to have been executed by the police, the Professor radios Palermo and declares [[DEFCON 2]] on the police. Part 3 concludes by showing Lisbon alive and in custody, and Tokyo narrating that the Professor had fallen for his own trap and that \"the war had begun.\"\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n\n=== Main ===\n<!-- Main and recurring are split and ordered as they appear in the series' credits. -->\n* [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]] as Silene Oliveira (Tokyo): the narrator; she was a runaway robber until scouted by the Professor to participate in his plan.\n* [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]] as Raquel Murillo (Lisbon): an inspector of the [[National Police Corps]] who is put in charge of the case until she joins the group in part 3.\n* [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]] as Sergio Marquina (The Professor / Salvador \"Salva\" Mart\u00edn): the mastermind of the heist who assembled the group, and Berlin's brother.\n* [[Paco Tous]] as Agust\u00edn Ramos (Moscow) (part 1\u20132; featured part 3): a former miner turned criminal and Denver's father.\n* [[Pedro Alonso]] as Andr\u00e9s de Fonollosa (Berlin): a terminally ill jewel thief and the Professor's second-in-command and brother.\n* [[Alba Flores]] as \u00c1gata Jim\u00e9nez (Nairobi): an expert in forgery in charge of printing the money for the group.\n* [[Miguel Herr\u00e1n]] as An\u00edbal Cort\u00e9s (Rio): a young hacker and Tokyo's boyfriend.\n* [[Jaime Lorente]] as Daniel/Ricardo{{efn|The official website lists Denver's name as Daniel,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/noticias/conoce-los-verdaderos-nombres-de-la-banda-de-atracadores-de-la-casa-de-papel_201711255a1940100cf2f56e3ec268dd.html |title=Conoce los verdaderos nombres de la banda de atracadores de 'La casa de papel' |language=es |publisher=antena3.com |last=\u00c1lvarez |first=Jennifer |date=25 November 2017 |access-date=16 August 2019}}</ref> but in the show he has called himself Ricardo.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Part 2, episode 8 |series=Money Heist |network=Netflix <!--|season= |series-no= |number=--> |time=36:50 |quote= |language=}}</ref>}} Ramos (Denver): Moscow's son who joins him in the heist.\n* [[Esther Acebo]] as M\u00f3nica Gaztambide (Stockholm): one of the hostages who is Arturo Rom\u00e1n's secretary and mistress, carrying his child out of wedlock. During the robbery, she falls in love with Denver and becomes an accomplice to the group.\n* [[Enrique Arce]] as Arturo Rom\u00e1n: a hostage and the Director of the [[Royal Mint of Spain]].\n* [[Mar\u00eda Pedraza]] as Alison Parker (part 1\u20132): a hostage and daughter of the British ambassador to Spain.\n* [[Darko Peri\u0107 (actor)|Darko Peri\u0107]] as Yashin Das\u00e1yev (Helsinki): a veteran Serbian soldier and Oslo's cousin.\n* [[Kiti M\u00e1nver]] as Mariv\u00ed Fuentes (part 1\u20132; featured part 3): Raquel's mother.\n* Hovik Keuchkerian as Bogot\u00e1 (part 3): an expert in metallurgy who joins the robbery of the [[Bank of Spain]].\n* [[Rodrigo de la Serna]] as Mart\u00edn (Palermo / The Engineer) (part 3): an old friend of Berlin's who planned the robbery of the Bank of Spain with him and assumes his place as commanding officer.\n* [[Najwa Nimri]] as Alicia Sierra (part 3): a pregnant inspector of the National Police Corps put in charge of the case after Raquel's departure from the force.\n\n=== Recurring ===\n* Roberto Garcia Ruiz as Dimitri Mostov\u00f3i / Radko Dragi\u0107{{efn|The final closing credits reveal Oslo's [[mug shot]] with the name Dimitri Mostov\u00f3i,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Part 2, episode 9 |series=Money Heist |network=Netflix <!--|season= |series-no= |number=--> |time=43:50 |quote= |language=}}</ref> while his coffin shows the name Radko Dragic.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Part 2, episode 8 |series=Money Heist |network=Netflix <!--|season= |series-no= |number=--> |time=24:00 |quote= |language=}}</ref>}} (Oslo) (part 1\u20132; featured part 3): a veteran Serbian soldier and Helsinki's cousin.\n* [[Fernando Soto (Spanish actor)|Fernando Soto]] as \u00c1ngel Rubio: a deputy inspector and Raquel's second-in-command.\n* Juan Fern\u00e1ndez as Colonel Prieto: a member of the Spanish Intelligence who oversees Raquel's work on the case.\n* Anna Gras as Mercedes Colmenar (part 1\u20132): Alison's teacher and one of the hostages.\n* Fran Morcillo as Pablo Ruiz (part 1): Alison's schoolmate and one of the hostages.\n* Clara Alvarado as Ariadna Cascales (part 1\u20132): one of the hostages who works in the Mint.\n* Mario de la Rosa as Su\u00e1rez: the chief of the [[Grupo Especial de Operaciones]].\n* Miquel Garc\u00eda Borda as Alberto Vicu\u00f1a (part 1\u20132): Raquel's ex-husband and a forensic examiner.\n* Naia Guz as Paula Vicu\u00f1a Murillo: Raquel and Alberto's daughter.\n* Luka Peros as Marseille (part 3): a member of the gang who joins the robbery of the Bank of Spain.\n* Fernando Cayo as Colonel Luis Tamayo (part 3): a member of the Spanish Intelligence who oversees Alicia's work on the case.\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Conception and writing ===\n\n{{further|#Themes and analysis}}\n\n{{Quote box |title= |quote=\"We wanted to make a very small project in a simple way; we wanted to cross lines we couldn't cross in previous projects, in terms of narrative and structure without any intermediaries.\" |author=\u2014Writer Esther Martinez Lobato |source=October 2018<ref name=dramaquarterly_181015 /> |align=right |width=30% |bgcolor=lightblue }}\n\nThe series was conceived by screenwriter [[\u00c1lex Pina]] and director Jes\u00fas Colmenar during their years of collaboration since 2008.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> After finishing their work on the Spanish prison drama [[Locked Up (TV series)|''Vis a vis'' (''Locked Up'')]], they left Globomedia to set up their own production company, named Vancouver Media, in 2016.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /><ref name=elespanol_170522>{{cite web |last=Jabonero |first=Daniel |url=https://www.elespanol.com/bluper/noticias/dificultades-fox-producir-tercera-temporada-vis-a-vis |title=Las dificultades que tiene FOX para producir una tercera temporada de \u2018Vis a Vis\u2019 |language=es |publisher=elespanol.com |date=22 May 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> For their first project, they considered either filming a comedy or developing a heist story for television,<ref name=elperiodico_190718>{{cite web |last=Fern\u00e1ndez |first=Juan |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/tele/20190718/la-casa-papel-somos-frikis-7557292 |title=Los de 'La casa de papel' somos unos frikis |language=es |publisher=elperiodico.com |date=18 July 2019 |access-date=17 August 2019}}</ref> with the latter having never been attempted before on Spanish television.<ref name=elconfidencial_170103>{{cite web |last=Galv |first=Marian |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-01-03/la-casa-de-papel-ursula-corbero-alba-flores-miguel-herran-paco-tous_1311689/ |title='La Casa de Papel' ficha a \u00darsula Corber\u00f3, Alba flores, Miguel Herr\u00e1n y Paco Tous |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=3 January 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref>  Along with former ''Locked Up'' colleagues,{{efn|''Locked Up'' and ''Money Heist'' share \u00c1lex Pina, Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato, Pablo Roa, and Esther Morales as writers; and Jes\u00fas Colmenar and Alex Rodrigo as directors.}} they developed ''Money Heist'' as a passion project to try new things without outside interference.<ref name=dramaquarterly_181015>{{cite web |url=https://dramaquarterly.com/pier-pressure/ |title=Pier pressure |publisher=dramaquarterly.com |date=15 October 2018 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref> Pina was firm about making it a limited series, feeling that dilution had become a problem for his previous productions.<ref name=elmundo_171016 />\n\nInitially entitled ''Los Desahuciados'' ({{transl|es|IAST|The Evicted}}) in the conception phase,<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> the series was developed to subvert heist conventions and combine elements of the [[action genre]], [[thrillers]] and [[surrealism]], while still being credible.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> Pina saw an advantage over typical heist films in that character development could span a considerably longer narrative arc.<ref name=partiv>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/global/money-heist-la-casa-de-papel-creator-alex-pina-10-takes-part-3-2-1203267428/|title=\u2018Money Heist\u2019 \u2013 \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 \u2013 Creator Alex Pina: 10 Takes on Part 3 |publisher=variety.com |last2=Hopewell |first2=John |last=Lang |first=Jamie |date=15 July 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> Characters were to be shown from multiple sides to break the viewers' preconceptions of villainy and retain their interest throughout the show.<ref name=partiv /> Key aspects of the planned storyline were written down at the beginning,<ref name=elmundo_190719>{{cite web |last=Elidrissi |first=Fati |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2019/07/19/5d30b25ffc6c83400d8b4622.html |title=La casa de papel: el fen\u00f3meno global espa\u00f1ol que retroalimenta la ficci\u00f3n |language=es |publisher=elmundo.es |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> while the finer story beats were developed incrementally to not overwhelm the writers.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander compared the writing process to the Professor's way of thinking, \"going around, writing down options, consulting engineers whom you cannot tell why you ask them that\", but noted that fiction allowed the police to be written dumber when necessary.<ref name=elmundo_190912 />\n\nThe beginning of filming was set for January 2017,<ref name=elconfidencial_170103 /> allowing for five months of pre-production.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The narrative was split into two parts for financial considerations.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The robbers' city-based code names, which Spanish newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' compared to the colour-based code names in [[Quentin Tarantino]]'s 1992 heist film ''[[Reservoir Dogs]]'',<ref name=abc_190716>{{cite web |last=Jim\u00e9nez |first=Alex |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-casa-papel-claves-exito-imparable-casa-papel-triunfa-todo-mundo-mano-netflix-201907160132_noticia.html |title=Las claves del \u00e9xito imparable de \"La casa de papel\", que triunfa en todo el mundo de la mano de Netflix |language=es |publisher=elperiodico.com |date=16 July 2019 |access-date=22 September 2019}}</ref> were chosen at random in the first part,<ref name=elperiodico_190627>{{cite web |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/yotele/20190627/netflix-confirma-cuarta-temporada-casa-papel-7524435 |title=Netflix confirma la cuarta temporada de 'La casa de papel' |language=es |publisher=[[El Peri\u00f3dico de Catalunya|elperiodico.com]] |date=27 June 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> although places with high viewership resonance were also taken into account for the new robbers' code names in part 3.<ref name=xataka_190705 /> The first five lines of the pilot script took a month to write,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> as the writers were unable to make the Professor or Moscow work as narrator.<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> Tokyo as an [[unreliable narrator]], flashbacks and time-jumps increased the narrative complexity,<ref name=partiv /> but also made the story more fluid for the audience.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The pilot episode required over 50 script versions until the producers were satisfied.<ref name=elpais_lcdp /><ref name=lanacion_190616>{{cite web |last=Ventura |first=Laura |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/de-visita-en-el-rodaje-de-la-nueva-casa-de-papel-nid2257022 |title=De visita en el rodaje de la nueva Casa de papel |language=es |publisher=lanacion.com.ar |date=16 June 2019 |access-date=23 September 2019}}</ref> Later scripts would be finished once per week to keep up with filming.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 />\n\n=== Casting ===\nCasting took place late in 2016, spanning more than two months.<ref name=abc_170628 /> The characters were not fully fleshed out at the beginning of this process, and took shape based on the actors' performance.<ref name=tercer_grado /> Casting directors Eva Leira and Yolanda Serrano were looking for actors with the ability to play empathetic robbers with believable love and family connections.<ref name=20minutos_190204>{{cite web |url=https://www.20minutos.com.mx/noticia/476793/0/eva-leira-y-yolanda-serrano-buscan-el-alma-del-actor-para-sus-series |title=Eva Leira y Yolanda Serrano buscan el alma del actor para sus series |publisher=[[20minutos]].com.mx |language=es |date=4 February 2019 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref> Antena 3 announced the ensemble cast in March 2017<ref name=antenacast>{{cite web |url=https://www.antena3.com/series/casa-de-papel/noticias/ursula-corbero-alba-flores-alvaro-morte-protagonistas-fiction-stories-%E2%80%98la-casa-papel%E2%80%99_2017032158d17ba20cf201b3e54261b1.html |title=\u00darsula Corber\u00f3, Alba Flores and \u00c1lvaro Morte, protagonists of the fiction stories of 'La Casa de Papel' |website=antena3.com |date=21 March 2017 |accessdate=20 August 2019 |language=es}}</ref> and released audition excerpts of most cast actors in the series' aftershow ''Tercer Grado'' and on their website.<ref name=tercer_grado />\n\nThe Professor was designed as a charismatic yet shy villain who could convince the robbers to follow him and make the audience sympathetic to the robbers' resistance against the powerful banks.<ref name=laprensa_190809>{{cite web |last=Ruiz de Elvira |first=\u00c1lvaro |url=https://laprensa.peru.com/espectaculos/noticia-casa-papel-parte-3-fecha-estreno-netflix-y-todo-lo-que-se-sabe-hasta-ahora-temporada-3-nnda-lt-78426 |title=La Casa de Papel, temporada 3: fecha de estreno en Netflix, tr\u00e1iler, historia, sinopsis, personajes, actores y todo sobre la Parte 3 |language=es |publisher=laprensa.peru.com |date=13 July 2018 |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref> However, developing the Professor's role proved difficult, as the character did not follow archetypal conventions<ref name=abc_170628 /> and the producers were uncertain about his degree of brilliance.<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> While the producers found his Salva personality early on,<ref name=elmundo_171016 /> they were originally looking for a 50-year-old [[Harvard]] professor type with the looks of Spanish actor [[Jos\u00e9 Coronado]].<ref name=esquire_190125 /><ref name=elmundo_171016 /> The role was proposed to [[Javier Guti\u00e9rrez \u00c1lvarez|Javier Guti\u00e9rrez]], but he was already committed to starring in the film ''[[Champions (2018 film)|Campeones]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-actor-realidad-iba-profesor-lugar-alvaro-morte-nnda-nnlt-noticia-681470-noticia/ |title=\"La casa de papel\": \u00bfqui\u00e9n es el actor que en realidad iba a ser el Profesor en lugar de \u00c1lvaro Morte? |language=es |publisher=elcomercio.pe |date=5 November 2019 |accessdate=6 November 2019}}</ref> Meanwhile, the casting directors advocated for [[\u00c1lvaro Morte]], whom they knew from their collaboration on the long-running Spanish soap opera ''[[El secreto de Puente Viejo]]'', even though his prime time television experience was limited at that point.<ref name=esquire_190125>{{cite web |last=P\u00e9rez |first=Ana |url=https://www.esquire.com/es/actualidad/tv/a26006005/alvaro-morte-la-casa-de-papel-3-temporada-el-embarcadero/ |title=Hablamos de series con 'El profesor' \u00c1lvaro Morte |language=es |publisher=esquire.com |date=25 January 2019 |accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref> Going through the full casting process and approaching the role through external analysis rather than personal experience, Morte described the professor as \"a tremendous box of surprises\" that \"end up shaping this character because he never ceases to generate uncertainty\", making it unclear for the audience if the character is good or bad.<ref name=abc_170628 /> The producers also found that his appearance of a primary school teacher gave the character more credibility.<ref name=elmundo_171016 />\n\n[[Pedro Alonso]] was cast to play Berlin, whom ''[[La Voz de Galicia]]'' would later characterize as a \"cold, hypnotic, sophisticated and disturbing character, an inveterate macho with serious empathy problems, a white-collar thief who despises his colleagues and considers them inferior.\"<ref name=lavozdegalicia_170503 /> The actor's portrayal of the character was inspired by a chance encounter Alonso had the day before receiving his audition script, with \"an intelligent person\" who was \"provocative or even manipulative\" to him.<ref name=lefigaro_180621>{{cite web |last=Perrin |first=\u00c9lisabeth |url=http://tvmag.lefigaro.fr/programme-tv/pedro-alonso-la-casa-de-papel-berlin-est-a-la-fois-cruel-heroique-et-drole-_88de13be-749a-11e8-8a00-24b61b86dc61/ |title=Pedro Alonso (La casa de papel) : \"Berlin est \u00e0 la fois cruel, h\u00e9ro\u00efque et dr\u00f4le\" |language=fr |publisher=lefigaro.fr |date=21 June 2018 |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref> Alonso saw high observation skills and an unusual understanding of his surroundings in Berlin, resulting in unconventional and unpredictable character behaviour.<ref name=lavozdegalicia_170503>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/television/2017/05/03/casa-papel-berlin/00031493797995350336283.htm |title=\"La casa de papel\": \u00bfQui\u00e9n es Berl\u00edn? |language=es |publisher=lavozdegalicia.es |date=3 May 2017 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref> Similarities between Berlin and [[Najwa Nimri]]'s character Zulema in Pina's TV series ''[[Locked Up (TV series)|Locked Up]]'' were unintentional.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/20170509/422415395188/la-casa-de-papel-antena-3-alex-pina.html |title=\u00bfC\u00f3mo se planifica el atraco perfecto de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019? |language=es |publisher=lavanguardia.com |date=9 May 2017 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref> The family connections between the Professor and Berlin were not in the original script, but were built into the characters' backstory at the end of part 1 after Morte and Alonso had repeatedly proposed to do so.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bravo |first=Vict\u00f3ria |url=https://www.metrojornal.com.br/entretenimento/2019/08/06/la-casa-de-papel-atores-revelam-como-mudaram-o-futuro-da-serie-mesmo-sem-o-consentimento-dos-criadores.html |title=La Casa de Papel: Atores revelam como mudaram o futuro da s\u00e9rie mesmo sem o consentimento dos criadores |language=pt |publisher=metrojornal.com.br |date=6 August 2019 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe producers found the protagonist and narrator, Tokyo, among the hardest characters to develop,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629>{{cite web |last=Pickard |first=Michael |url=https://dramaquarterly.com/hold-up/ |title=Right on the Money |publisher=dramaquarterly.com |date=29 June 2018 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref> as they were originally looking for an older actress to play the character who had nothing to lose before meeting the Professor.<ref name=tercer_grado/> [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]] eventually landed the role for bringing a playful energy to the table; her voice was heavily factored in during casting, as she was the first voice the audience hears in the show.<ref name=tercer_grado /> [[Jaime Lorente]] developed Denver's hallmark laughter during the casting process.<ref name=tercer_grado /> Two cast actors had appeared in previous TV series by \u00c1lex Pina: [[Paco Tous]] (Moscow) had starred in the 2010 TV series ''[[Los hombres de Paco]]'', and [[Alba Flores]] (Nairobi) had starred starred in ''Locked Up''. Flores was asked to play Nairobi without audition when Pina realized late in the conception phase that the show needed another female gang member.<ref name=elmundo_171016>{{cite web |last=Gasparyan |first=Suren |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2017/10/16/59e22acf468aeb9c3f8b45d5.html |title=Una 'casa de papel' con dos 'profesores' |language=es |publisher=elmundo.es |date=16 October 2017 |accessdate=13 September 2019}}</ref> For the role opposite to the robbers, [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]] was cast to play Inspector Raquel Murillo, whom Itu\u00f1o described as a \"strong and powerful woman in a world of men, but also sensitive in her private life\".<ref name=repubblica_180923>{{cite web |last=Echites |first=Giulia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/serie/2018/09/23/news/l_ispettor_murillo_de_la_casa_di_carta_la_mia_raquel_donna_forte_in_un_mondo_di_uomini_-207157309/ |title=L'ispettore Murillo de 'La casa di carta': \"La mia Raquel, donna forte in un mondo di uomini\" |language=it |publisher=repubblica.it |date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=30 September 2019}}</ref> She took inspiration from ''[[The Silence of the Lambs (novel)|The Silence of the Lambs]]'' character [[Clarice Starling]], an FBI student with a messy family life who develops sympathies for a criminal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wradio.com.co/noticias/sociedad/la-tercera-parte-de-la-serie-sera-un-bombazo-itziar-ituno-actriz-de-la-casa-de-papel/20180418/nota/3738979.aspx |title=La tercera parte de la serie ser\u00e1 un \"bombazo\": Itziar Itu\u00f1o, actriz de \"La casa de papel\" |language=es |publisher=wradio.com.co |date=18 April 2018 |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe actors learned of the show's renewal by Netflix before the producers contacted them to return.<ref>{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Livia |url=https://rpp.pe/tv/netflix/la-casa-de-papel-itziar-ituno-confirma-que-raquel-murillo-estara-en-la-tercera-temporada-noticia-1134985 |title=\"La Casa de Papel\": Itziar Itu\u00f1o confirma que Raquel Murillo estar\u00e1 en la tercera temporada |website=[[as.com]] |date=9 July 2018 |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref> In October 2018, Netflix announced the cast of part 3; the returning main cast included Pedro Alonso, raising speculation about his role in part 3.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/global/la-casa-de-papel-part-3-production-watch-video-1202993850/ |publisher=variety.com |title=\u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 Part 3 Goes into Production: Watch Video |date=25 October 2018 |accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> Among the new cast members were Argentine actor [[Rodrigo de la Serna]], who saw a possible connection between his character's name and the Argentine football legend [[Mart\u00edn Palermo]],<ref>{{cite web |first=\u00c1. |last= Jim\u00e9nez |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-casa-papel-motivo-palermo-llama-casa-papel-201907300136_noticia.html |title=El motivo por el que Palermo se llama as\u00ed en \"La casa de papel\" |website=abc.es |date=30 July 2019 |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref> and ''Locked Up'' star Najwa Nimri. Cameo scenes of Brazilian football star, and fan of the series, [[Neymar]], as a monk were filmed for part 3, but were excluded from the stream without repercussions to the narrative until judicial charges against him had been dropped in late August 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Galarraga Gort\u00e1zar |first=Naiara |url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2019/09/04/inenglish/1567586223_216483.html |title=Neymar makes cameo in Netflix hit \u2018Money Heist\u2019 after rape case dropped |website=elpais.com |date=4 September 2019 |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=elmundo_190912 /> A small appearance by Spanish actress [[Bel\u00e9n Cuesta]] in two episodes of part 3 raised fan and media speculation about her role in part 4.<ref>{{cite web |first=V\u00edctor |last=Mill\u00e1n |url=https://as.com/epik/2019/08/04/portada/1564907334_831996.html |title='La Casa de Papel': \u00bfQu\u00e9 significa el papel de 'extra' de Bel\u00e9n Cuesta? |website=[[as.com]] |date=5 August 2019 |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Production design ===\n\n[[File:Salvador Dali NYWTS.jpg|thumb|upright|Spanish Surrealist painter [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]] was chosen as the heist team's mask design.]]\n\nThe show's look and atmosphere were developed by creator \u00c1lex Pina, director Jes\u00fas Colmenar, and director of photography Migue Amoedo, according to ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' \"the most prolific television trio in recent years\".<ref name=lavanguardia_190719>{{cite web |last=Sol\u00e0 Gimferrer |first=Pere |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/netflix/20190719/463580297705/la-casa-de-papel-claves-exito-serie-netflix.html |title=Las claves del \u00e9xito de La casa de papel |language=es |publisher=lavanguardia.com |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> Abd\u00f3n Alca\u00f1iz served as art director.<ref name=alicanteplaza_180612 /> Their collaboration projects usually take a primary colour as a basis;<ref name=alicanteplaza_180612>{{cite web |last=Vi\u00f1as |first=Eugenio |url=https://alicanteplaza.es/AbdnAlcaizelvalencianotrasladireccindeartedealgunasdelasgrandesseriesespaolas |title=Abd\u00f3n Alca\u00f1iz, el valenciano tras la direcci\u00f3n de arte de algunas de las grandes series espa\u00f1olas |language=es |publisher=elpais.com |date=12 June 2018 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> ''Money Heist'' had red as \"one of the distinguishing features of the series\"<ref name=elpais_170503 /> that stood over the gray sets.<ref name=elpais_190711 /> Blue, green and yellow were marked as a forbidden colour in production design.<ref name=elpais_190711>{{Cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/07/11/television/1562847443_895744.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 derrocha poder\u00edo en su regreso |language=es |date=12 July 2019 |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=elpais.com |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> To achieve \"absolute film quality\", red tones were tested with different types of fabrics, textures and lighting.<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> The iconography of the robbers' red jumpsuits mirrored the yellow prison dress code in ''Locked Up''.<ref name=elpais_170503>{{cite web |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2017/05/03/television/1493765342_705803.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 se atreve |language=es |publisher=elpais.com |date=3 May 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> For part 3, the Italian retail clothing company [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]] modified the red jumpsuits to better fit the body and launched a clothing line inspired by the series.<ref name=elpais_190711 /> [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]] was chosen as the robbers' mask design because of Dal\u00ed's recognisable visage that also serves as an iconic cultural reference to Spain; [[Don Quixote]] as an alternative mask design was discarded.<ref name=elpais_180712>{{cite web |last=Ruiz de Elvira |first=\u00c1lvaro |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2018/07/12/television/1531403342_602750.html |title=\u00c1lex Pina: \"Hay que hacer avances en la ficci\u00f3n, el espectador es cada vez m\u00e1s experto\" |language=es |publisher=elpais.com |date=13 July 2018 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> This choice sparked criticism by the [[Gala-Salvador Dal\u00ed Foundation]] for not requesting the necessary permissions.<ref name=20minutos_190204 />\n\nTo make the plot more realistic, the producers requested and received advice from the national police and the Spanish Ministry of Interior.<ref name=elmundo_170502 /><ref>{{cite web |last=Molina |first=Berto |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-05-08/casa-de-papel-serie-antena-3-fabrica-nacional-moneda-timbre-atraco_1379218/ |title=La F\u00e1brica de la Moneda, molesta con la trama de la serie 'La casa de papel' |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=8 May 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> The robbers' banknotes were printed with permission of the [[Bank of Spain]] and had an increased size as an anti-counterfeit measure.<ref name=elmundo_170502>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elmundo.es/television/2017/05/02/59077570ca474185328b463d.html |title=Todo el dinero de La casa de papel |language=es |date=2 May 2017 |last=Gago |first=Claudia |website=elmundo.es |access-date=9 September 2019}}</ref> The greater financial backing of Netflix for part 3 allowed for the build of over 50 sets across five basic filming locations world-wide.<ref name=publimetro_190711 /> Preparing a remote and uninhabited island in [[Panama]] to represent a robber hide-out proved difficult, as it needed to be cleaned, secured and built on, and involved hours-long travelling with material transportation.<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> The real Bank of Spain was unavailable for visiting and filming for security reasons, so the producers recreated the Bank on a two-level stage by their own imagining, taking inspiration from Spanish architecture of the [[Francisco Franco]] era.<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> Publicly available information was used to make the Bank's main hall set similar to the real location. The other interior sets were inspired by different periods and artificially aged to accentuate the building's history.<ref name=publimetro_190711 /> [[Bronze]] and [[granite]] sculptures and motifs from the [[Valle de los Ca\u00eddos]] were recreated for the interior,<ref name=sensacine_190617>{{cite web |last=Romero |first=Marta A. |url=http://www.sensacine.com/noticias/series/noticia-18577464/ |title='La casa de papel' nos abre sus puertas: te contamos c\u00f3mo se ha rodado la tercera temporada con Netflix |language=es |publisher=sensacine.com |date=17 June 2019 |access-date=18 September 2019}}</ref> and over 50 paintings were painted for the Bank to emulate the [[Ateneo de Madrid]].<ref name=publimetro_190711>{{cite web |last=Cordovez |first=Karen |url=https://www.publimetro.cl/cl/entretenimiento/2019/07/11/la-casa-papel-los-secretos-del-rodaje-la-tercera-temporada.html |title=\"La Casa de Papel\": los secretos del rodaje de la tercera temporada |language=es |publisher=publimetro.cl |date=11 July 2019 |access-date=18 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n\n[[File:Edificio central del CSIC (Madrid) 02.jpg|thumb|right|240px|The [[Spanish National Research Council]] headquarters, the principal filming location of part 1 and 2 of ''Money Heist'']]\n[[File:Madrid - Nuevos Ministerios 03.JPG|thumb|right|240px|The [[Nuevos Ministerios]], the principal filming location of part 3 of ''Money Heist'']]\n\nParts 1 and 2 were filmed back-to-back in the greater [[Madrid]] region from January until August 2017.<ref name=abc_170628 /><ref name=lavanguardia_190807>{{Cite web |first=Molly |last=Antigone Hall |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/ocio/viajes/20190807/463750726691/lugares-rodaje-casa-de-papel.html |title=Este es el Madrid real de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |date=7 August 2019 |website=lavanguardia.com |access-date=9 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=elpais_lcdp /> The pilot episode was recorded in 26 days,<ref name=elmundo_170502 /> while all other episodes had around 14 filming days.<ref name=partiv/> Production was split into two units to save time, with one unit shooting scenes involving the Professor and the police, and the other filming scenes with the robbers.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> The main storyline is set in the [[Royal Mint (Spain)|Royal Mint of Spain]] in Madrid, but the exterior scenes were filmed at the [[Spanish National Research Council]] (CSIC) headquarters for its passing resemblance to the Mint,<ref name=elmundo_170502 /> and on the roof of the Higher Technical School of Aeronautical Engineers, part of the [[Technical University of Madrid]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190807 /> The hunting estate where the robbers plan their coup was filmed at the Finca El Gasco farm estate in [[Torrelodones]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190807 /> Interior filming took place at the former ''[[Locked Up (TV series)|Locked Up]]'' sets in [[Colmenar Viejo]]<ref name=elespanol_170522 /> and at the Spanish national daily newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' in [[Torrej\u00f3n de Ardoz]] for printing press scenes.<ref name=elpais_lcdp>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elpais.com.co/especiales/la-casa-de-papel/ |title=La historia detr\u00e1s del \u00e9xito |language=es |website=elpais.com.co |access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref> As the show was designed as a limited series, all sets were destroyed once production of part 2 had finished.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 />\n\nParts 3 and 4 were also filmed back-to-back,<ref name=elcomercio_190808 /> with 21 to 23 filming days per episode.<ref name=partiv/> Netflix announced the start of filming on 25 October 2018,<ref name=laprensa_190809 /> and filming of part 4 ended in August 2019.<ref name=p4filmend /> In 2018, Netflix had opened their first European production hub in [[Tres Cantos]] near Madrid for new and existing Netflix productions;<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hopewell |first=John |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/netflix-european-production-hub-madrid-1202882341/ |title=Netflix Launches Its First European Production Hub in Madrid |date=24 July 2018 |website=elpais.com |access-date=10 September 2019}}</ref> main filming moved there onto a set three times the size of the set used for parts 1 and 2.<ref name=elpais_190614 /> The main storyline is set in the [[Bank of Spain]] in Madrid, but the exterior was filmed at the Ministry of Development complex [[Nuevos Ministerios]].<ref name=elpais_190614>{{Cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/06/14/television/1560524898_475068.html |title=\"La serie es m\u00e1s grande\": dentro de la nueva temporada de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |date=17 June 2019 |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=elpais.com |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> A scene where money is dropped from the sky was filmed at [[Callao Square]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190807 /> {{Interlanguage link|Ermita de San Frutos|es|Ermita de San Frutos (Carrascal del R\u00edo)}} in [[Carrascal del R\u00edo]] served as the exterior of the Italian monastery where the robbers plan the heist.<ref name=elpais_190711 /> The motorhome scenes of the Professor and Lisboa were filmed at the deserted Las Salinas beaches in [[Almer\u00eda]] to make the audience feel that the characters are safe from the police although their exact location is undisclosed at first.<ref name=lavanguardia_191117 /> Underwater scenes inside the vault were filmed at [[Pinewood Studios]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite AV media |people=Flores, Alba |date=4 October 2019 |title=Escena Favorita: Alba Flores \u2013 La Casa de Papel \u2013 Netflix |language=es |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=glP9VPzxZnY |access-date=7 October 2019 |time=0:30 |publisher= La Casa De Papel at youtube.com}}</ref><ref name=xataka_190705 /> The beginning of part 3 was also filmed in [[Thailand]], on the [[Guna Yala]] islands in [[Panama]], and in [[Florence]], Italy,<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> which helped to counter the claustrophobic feeling of the first two parts,<ref name=partiv /> but was also an expression of the plot's global repercussions.<ref name=elespectador_190718 />\n\n=== Music ===\n\nThe series' theme song, \"My Life Is Going On\", was composed by Manel Santisteban, who also served as composer on ''Locked Up''. Santisteban approached Spanish singer Cecilia Krull to write and perform the lyrics, which are about having confidence in one's abilities and the future.<ref name=oprahmag_190722>{{cite web |url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a28468639/la-casa-de-papel-money-heist-theme-song/ |title=The Theme Song for Netflix's La Casa de Papel/Money Heist Sends a Deliberate Message |date=22 July 2019 |last=Fernandez |first=Celia |publisher=oprahmag.com |access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref> The theme song is played behind a title sequence featuring paper models of major settings from the series.<ref name=oprahmag_190722 /> Krull's main source of inspiration was the character Tokyo in the first episode of the series, when the Professor offers her a way out of a desperate moment.<ref name=lavoz_190917 /> The lyrics are in English as the language that came naturally to Krull at the time of writing.<ref name=lavoz_190917>{{cite web |url=https://vos.lavoz.com.ar/musica/cecilia-krull-la-voz-por-detras-de-la-cancion-de-la-casa-de-papel |title=Cecilia Krull, la voz por detr\u00e1s de la canci\u00f3n de \"La casa de papel\" |date=17 September 2019 |last=Rojas |first=Rodrigo |publisher=vos.lavoz.com.ar |language=es |access-date=25 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Italian [[anti-fascist]] song \"[[Bella ciao]]\" plays multiple times throughout the series and accompanies two emblematic key scenes: At the end of the first part the Professor and Berlin sing it in preparation for the heist, embracing themselves as resistance against the establishment,<ref name=faz_180802>{{Cite web |url=https://www.faz.net/aktuell/gesellschaft/menschen/bella-ciao-und-die-netflix-serie-haus-des-geldes-15719916.html |title=\"Wie \"Bella Ciao\" zum Sommerhit wurde |language=de |last=Wiesner |first=Maria |date=2 August 2018 |access-date=14 August 2019 |publisher=[[faz.net]]}}</ref> and in the second part it plays during the thieves' escape from the Mint, as a metaphor for freedom.<ref name=\"bellaciao\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vix.com/pt/series/555595/bella-ciao-musica-em-la-casa-de-papel-e-antiga-mas-tem-tudo-a-ver-com-a-serie |title=\"Bella Ciao\": m\u00fasica em \"La Casa de Papel\" \u00e9 antiga, mas tem TUDO a ver com a s\u00e9rie |language=pt |date=19 February 2018 |last=Pereira |first=Alien |publisher=vix.com |access-date=14 August 2019}}</ref> Regarding the use of the song, Tokyo recounts in one of her narrations, \"The life of the Professor revolved around a single idea: Resistance. His grandfather, who had [[Italian resistance movement|fought against the fascists in Italy]], taught him the song and he taught us.\"<ref name=\"bellaciao\" /> The song was brought to the show by writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander. He had listened to \"Bella ciao\" at home to cheer him up, as he had grown frustrated for not finding a suitable song for the middle of part 1.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> He was aware of the song's meaning and history and felt it represented positive values.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> \"Bella ciao\" became a summer hit in Europe in 2018, mostly due to the popularity of the series and not the song's grave themes.<ref name=faz_180802 />\n\n== Themes and analysis ==\n\nThe series was noted for its subversions of the [[heist genre]]. While heist films are usually told with a rational male Anglo-centric focus, the series reframes the heist story by giving it a strong [[Spaniard|Spanish]] identity and telling it from a female perspective through Tokyo.<ref name=lavozdeasturias_190126>{{cite web |last=Vidal |first=Mar\u00eda |url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/cultura/2019/01/26/embarcadero-tenia-presion-casa-papel/0003_201901SY26P14991.htm |title=\u00c1lex Pina: \"Con 'El embarcadero' ten\u00eda m\u00e1s presi\u00f3n que con 'La Casa de Papel'\" |language=es |publisher=lavozdeasturias.es |date=4 February 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> The producers regarded the cultural identity as an important part of the personality of the series, as it made the story more relatable for viewers.<ref name=xataka_190705>{{cite web |last=Muela |first=Cesar |url=https://www.xataka.com/cine-y-tv/casa-papel-no-hubiera-estado-netflix-seguiriamos-diciendo-que-no-podemos-competir-series-fuera-alex-pina-creador-serie |title=\"Si 'La Casa de Papel' no hubiera estado en Netflix seguir\u00edamos diciendo que no podemos competir con las series de fuera\", \u00c1lex Pina, creador de la serie |publisher=xataka.com |language=es |date=3 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> They also avoided adapting the series to international tastes,<ref name=xataka_190705 /> which helped to set it apart from the usual American TV series<ref name=elespanol_190724 /> and raised international awareness of Spanish sensibilities.<ref name=xataka_190705 /> Emotional dynamics like the passion and impulsivity of friendship and love offset the perfect strategic crime for increased tension.<ref name=lavozdeasturias_190126 /><ref name=elcomercio_190808>{{cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-temporada-4-fecha-estreno-netflix-parte-4-trailer-historia-pasara-actores-personajes-money-heist-espana-ficha-tv-nnda-nnlt-noticia-650201 |title=\"La casa de papel\", temporada 4: fecha de estreno en Netflix, qu\u00e9 pasar\u00e1, actores, personajes, misterios y teor\u00edas |language=es |publisher=elcomercio.pe |date=10 August 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> Nearly all main characters, including the relationship-opposing Professor, eventually succumb to love,<ref name=elespectador_190718>{{cite web |last=Contreras Fajardo |first=Lilian |url=https://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/medios/la-casa-de-papel-3-robar-oro-para-recuperar-el-amor-articulo-871675 |title=\"La Casa de Papel 3\": robar oro para recuperar el amor |publisher=elespectador.com |language=es |date=18 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> for which the series received comparisons to [[telenovela]]s.<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /><ref name=theglobeandmail /> Comedic elements, which were compared to ''[[Back to the Future]]''<ref name=abc_170628>{{cite web |last=Soage |first=Noelia |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-entrevista-alvaro-morte-casa-papel-201706280112_noticia.html |title=\u00c1lvaro Morte: \"La casa de papel va a marcar un antes y un despu\u00e9s en la forma de tratar la ficci\u00f3n en este pa\u00eds\" |publisher=abc.es |language=es |date=28 June 2017 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> and [[black comedy]],<ref name=elpais_190614 /> also offset the heist tension.<ref name=variety_190801 /> The heist film formula is subverted by the heist starting straight after the opening credits instead of lingering on how the gang is brought together.<ref name=haaretz_180807>{{cite web |last=Hennigan |first=Adrian |url=https://www.haaretz.com/life/television/.premium-netflix-s-money-heist-will-steal-your-heart-and-your-weekend-1.5977887 |title=Netflix's 'Money Heist' Will Steal Your Heart and Your Weekend |publisher=[[haaretz.com]] |date=7 April 2018 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nWith the series being set after the [[financial crisis of 2007\u20132008]], which resulted in severe austerity measures in Spain,<ref name=theglobeandmail /> critics argued that the series was an explicit allegory of rebellion against capitalism,<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /><ref name=lemonde_190313>{{cite web |last=S\u00e9risier |first=Pierre |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/blog/seriestv/2018/03/13/la-casa-de-papel-allegorie-de-la-rebellion/ |title=La Casa de Papel \u2013 All\u00e9gorie de la r\u00e9bellion |language=fr |publisher=lemonde.fr |date=13 March 2018 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> including ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', who saw the series as \"subversive in that it's about a heist for the people. It's revenge against a government.\"<ref name=\"theglobeandmail\" /> According to ''[[Le Monde]]'', the Professor's teaching scenes in the Toledo hunting estate in particular highlighted how people should seek to develop their own solutions for the fallible capitalist system.<ref name=lemonde_190313 /> The show's [[Robin Hood]] analogy of robbing the rich and giving to the poor received various interpretations. ''[[El Espa\u00f1ol]]'' argued that the analogy made it easier for viewers to connect with the show, as modern society tended to be tired of banks and politics already,<ref name=elespanol_190724>{{cite web |last=Zurro |first=Javier |url=https://www.elespanol.com/cultura/series/20190724/netflix-no-tomes-pelo-casa-papel/415959462_0.html |title=Netflix, no nos tomes el pelo: 'La Casa de Papel' no es para tanto |language=es |publisher=elespanol.com|date=24 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> and ''The New Statesman'' said the rich were no longer stolen from but undermined at their roots.<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> On the other hand, [[Esquire (magazine)|''Esquire'']]'s Mireia Mullor saw the Robin Hood analogy as a mere distraction strategy for the robbers, as they initially did not plan to use the money from their first heist to improve the quality of life of regular people; for this reason, Mullor also argues that the large following for the robbers in part 3 was not comprehensible even though they represented a channel for the discontent of those bearing economic and political injustices.<ref name=esquire_190729>{{cite web |last=Mullor |first=Mireia |url=https://www.esquire.com/es/actualidad/tv/a28516581/la-casa-de-papel-temporada-3-critica-netflix/ |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019: Los pros y contras de la tercera temporada en Netflix |language=es |publisher=esquire.com |date=29 July 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe characters were designed as multi-dimensional and complementary [[antagonist]]s and [[anti-hero]]es whose moralities are ever-changing.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> Examples include Berlin, who shifts from a robber mistreating hostages, to one of the series' most beloved characters.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> There is also the hostage M\u00f3nica Gaztambide, as well as inspector Raquel Murillo, who eventually join the cause of the robbers.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> Gonz\u00e1lvez of ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' finds that an audience may think of the robbers as evil at first for committing a crime, but as the series progresses it marks the financial system as the true evil and suggests the robbers have ethical and empathetic justification for stealing from an overpowered thief.<ref name=huffingtonpost_190628>{{cite web |last=Gonz\u00e1lvez |first=Paula M. |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.es/entry/por-que-arrasa-la-casa-de-papel-en-todo-el-mundo-cada-detalle-esta-estudiado_es_5d14ff66e4b03d6116385913 |title=Qu\u00e9 ha hecho bien 'La Casa de Papel' para convertirse en la serie de habla no inglesa m\u00e1s vista de la historia de Netflix |language=es |publisher=huffingtonpost.es |date=28 June 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> Najwa Nimri, playing inspector Sierra in part 3, said that \"the complex thing about a villain is giving him humanity. That's where everyone gets alarmed, when you have to prove that a villain also has a heart\". She added that the amount of information and technology that surrounds us is allowing us to verify that \"everyone has a dark side.\"<ref name=huffingtonpost_190628 /> The series leaves it to the audience to decide who is good or bad, as characters are \"relatable and immoral\" at various points in the story.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> Pina argued that it was this ability to change view that made the series addictive and marked its success.<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 />\n\nWith the relative number of female main characters in TV shows generally on the rise,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> the series gives female characters the same attention as men, which the [[BBC]] regarded as an innovation for Spanish television.<ref name=bbc_190312 /> While many plot lines in the heist series still relate to males,<ref name=dramaquarterly_180629 /> the female characters become increasingly aware of gender-related issues, such as M\u00f3nica arguing in part 3 that women, just like men, could be robbers and a good parent.<ref name=esquire_190722>{{cite web |last=Mart\u00edn |first=Cynthia |url=https://www.esquire.com/es/actualidad/a28443894/la-casa-de-papel-3-feminista-entrevista-alba-flores-darko-peric/ |title='La Casa de Papel 3' y su \"me too\" a la espa\u00f1ola |language=es |publisher=esquire.com |date=22 July 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Critics further examined [[feminist]] themes and a rejection of [[machismo]]<ref name=esquire_190722 /> in the series through Nairobi and her phrase \"The [[matriarchy]] begins\" in part 2,<ref name=publimetro_190719 /> and a comparative scene in part 3, where Palermo claims a [[patriarchy]] in a moment that, according to [[CNET]], is played for laughs.<ref name=cnet_190719>{{cite web |last=Puentes |first=Patricia |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/money-heist-3-netflix-review-bigger-heist-higher-stakes-same-red-coveralls/ |title=Money Heist 3 review: Bigger heist, higher stakes, same red coveralls |publisher=cnet.com |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=7 October 2019}}</ref> ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' challenged any female-empowering claims in the series, as \u00darsula Corber\u00f3 (Tokyo) was often shown scantily clad,<ref name=lavanguardia_190809>{{cite web |last=Sol\u00e0 Gimferrer |first=Pere |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/netflix/20190809/463948127016/la-casa-de-papel-tercera-parte-critica-presupuesto.html |title=Verdades inc\u00f3modas de series (I): La lecci\u00f3n de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |language=es |publisher=lavanguardia.com |date=9 August 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> and ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'' criticized how characters' relationship problems in part 3 were often portrayed to be the women's fault.<ref name=esquire_190729 /> Alba Flores (Nairobi) saw no inherent feminist plot in the series, as women only take control when it suits the story,<ref name=publimetro_190719>{{cite web |last=Cordovez |first=Karen |url=https://www.publimetro.cl/cl/entretenimiento/2019/07/19/nairobi-y-el-regreso-de-la-casa-de-papel-ahora-el-golpe-es-mas-ambicioso-porque-su-finalidad-es-mas-grande.html |title=\"Nairobi\" y el regreso de \"La Casa de Papel\": \"Ahora el golpe es m\u00e1s ambicioso porque su finalidad es m\u00e1s grande\" |language=es |publisher=publimetro.cl |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> whilst Esther Acebo (M\u00f3nica) described any feminist subtext in the show as not being vindictive.<ref name=huffingtonpost_190708>{{cite web |last=Gonz\u00e1lvez |first=Paula M. |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.es/entry/alvaro-morte-habia-un-rechazo-hacia-la-ficcion-espanola-por-el-mero-hecho-de-ser-espanola_es_5d14ec6be4b082e55365da00 |title=Najwa Nimri ('La Casa de Papel'): \"Tengo una experiencia clar\u00edsima con el \u00e9xito y si no te quieres exponer, no te expones\" |language=es |publisher=huffingtonpost.es |date=8 July 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n\n=== Original broadcast ===\n\n{{box\n| align = center\n|{{Television ratings graph\n<!--| title       = La Casa De Papel-->\n| country     = Antena 3\n| color1      = #A90712\n| color2      = #594022\n| average     = y\n| no_table = y\n| height = 200\n| bar_width   = 5\n| x_intervals = 5\n| y_intervals = 1\n| refs        = <ref>{{cite web |title=AUDIENCIAS LA CASA DE PAPEL |url=https://www.formulatv.com/series/la-casa-de-papel/audiencias/ |website=formulatv.com |accessdate=27 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180427032300/http://www.formulatv.com/series/la-casa-de-papel/audiencias/ |archivedate=27 April 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"La casa de papel\": La serie espa\u00f1ola que arrasa en el mundo |url=https://www.24horas.cl/tendencias/espectaculosycultura/la-casa-de-papel-la-serie-espanola-que-arrasa-en-el-mundo--2654256 |website=24horas.cl |accessdate=27 April 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| season_title = Part\n|-\n<!-- P01E01 -->| 4.090\n<!-- P01E02 -->| 3.041\n<!-- P01E03 -->| 2.646\n<!-- P01E04 -->| 2.655\n<!-- P01E05 -->| 2.366\n<!-- P01E06 -->| 2.474\n<!-- P01E07 -->| 2.420\n<!-- P01E08 -->| 2.070\n<!-- P01E09 -->| 2.196\n<!-- P01E10 -->| 1.995\n<!-- P01_AV -->| 2.595\n|-\n<!-- P02E11 -->| 1.737\n<!-- P02E12 -->| 1.571\n<!-- P02E13 -->| 1.539\n<!-- P02E14 -->| 1.487\n<!-- P02E15 -->| 1.80\n<!-- P02_AV -->| 1.627\n}}}}\n\nPart 1 aired on free-to-air Spanish TV channel [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] in the Wednesday 10:40&nbsp;p.m. time slot from 2 May 2017 till 27 June 2017.<ref name=elmundo_170502 /> Part 2 moved to the Monday 10:40&nbsp;p.m. time slot and was broadcast from 16 October 2017 till 23 November 2017,<ref name=elpais_171010>{{cite web |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2017/10/10/television/1507633357_409248.html |title=El atraco perfecto llega a su fin |website=elpais.com |language=es |date=15 October 2017 |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> with the originally planned 18-21 episodes cut down to 15.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /><ref name=eldario_170502>{{cite web |url=http://vertele.eldiario.es/noticias/entrevista-alex-pina-lacasadepapel-antena3_0_1897010292.html |title=\u00c1lex Pina presenta 'La casa de Papel': 'Vis a Vis fue un enorme banco de pruebas' |website=[[eldiario.es]] |language=es |date=2 May 2017 |access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref> As the series was developed with Spanish prime-time television in mind,<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> the episodes had a length of around 70 minutes, as is typical for Spanish television.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> The first five episodes of part 1 were followed by an [[aftershow]] entitled ''Tercer Grado'' ({{transl|es|IAST|Third Grade}}).<ref name=tercer_grado />\n\nDespite boycott calls after [[Itziar Itu\u00f1o]] (Raquel Murillo) had protested against the accommodations of [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] prisoners of her home [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country]] in March 2016,<ref>{{cite web |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-itziar-ituno-piden-boicot-casa-papel-apoyo-protagonistas-otegui-y-presos-etarras-201705031050_noticia.html |title=Piden el boicot a \"La casa de papel\" por el apoyo de una de sus protagonistas a Otegui y al acercamiento de presos etarras |website=abc.es |language=es |date=4 May 2017 |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> the show had the best premiere of a Spanish series since April 2015,<ref name=larazon_170621/> with more than four million viewers and the majority share of viewers in its timeslot, almost double the number of the next highest-viewed station/show.<ref name=bbc_190312>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20190312-la-casa-de-papel-setting-the-bar-for-global-television |title=La Casa de Papel: Setting the bar for global television |last=Keishin Armstrong |first=Jennifer |website=[[bbc.com]] |access-date=10 August 2019 |date=13 March 2019}}</ref> The show received good reviews and remained a leader in the commercial target group for the first half of part 1,<ref name=larazon_170621>{{cite web |url=https://www.larazon.es/tv-y-comunicacion/tv-news/una-espectacular-explosion-y-plan-de-fuga-de-los-rehenes-en-la-casa-de-papel-AB15419339 |title=Una espectacular explosi\u00f3n y plan de fuga de los rehenes, en \u2018La casa de papel\u2019  |website=[[larazon.es]] |access-date=27 September 2019 |date=21 June 2017}}</ref> but the viewership eventually slipped to lower figures than expected by the Antena 3 executives.<ref name=elpais_171124 /> Argentine newspaper ''[[La Naci\u00f3n]]'' attributed the decrease in viewer numbers to the change in time slots, the late broadcast times and the summer break between the parts.<ref name=lanacion_190616 /> Pina saw the commercial breaks as responsible, as they disrupted the narrative flow of the series that otherwise played almost in real time, even though the breaks were factored in during writing.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' saw the interest only waning among the conventional audience, as the plot unfolded too slowly at the rate of one episode per week.<ref name=lavanguardia_190719 /> Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander regarded the series' run on Antena 3 as a \"failure\" in 2019, as the ratings declined to \"nothing special\", but commended Antena 3 for making a series that did not rely on typical stand-alone episodes.<ref name=elmundo_190912>{{cite web |last=D\u00edas-Guerra |first=I\u00f1ako |url=https://www.elmundo.es/papel/cultura/2019/09/12/5d791951fc6c8337538b45fe.html |title=Javier G\u00f3mez Santander: \"Los espa\u00f1oles no somos un buen ej\u00e9rcito, pero como guerrilla somos la hostia\" |website=elmundo.es |language=es |date=12 September 2019 |access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Netflix acquisition ===\n\nPart 1 was made available on [[Netflix|Netflix Spain]] on 1 July 2017, like other series belonging to Antena 3's parent media group [[Atresmedia]].<ref name=larazon_170630>{{Cite web |url=https://www.larazon.es/tv-y-comunicacion/tv-news/netflix-se-fija-de-nuevo-en-una-serie-de-atresmedia-compra-la-casa-de-papel-para-emitirla-en-todo-el-mundo-NJ15494977 |title=Netflix se fija, de nuevo, en una serie de Atresmedia: compra 'La casa de papel' para emitirla en todo el mundo |website=larazon.es |language=es |date=30 June 2017 |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref> In December 2017, Netflix acquired the exclusive global streaming rights for the series.<ref name=bbc_190312 /><ref name=larazon_170630 /> Netflix re-cut the series into 22 episodes of around 50 minutes length.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Cliffhangers and scenes had to be divided and moved to other episodes, but this proved less drastic than expected because of the series' perpetual plot twists.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Netflix [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbed]] the series and renamed it from ''La casa de papel'' to ''Money Heist'' for distribution in the English-speaking world,<ref name=bbc_190312 /> releasing the first part on 20 December 2017 without any promotion.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /><ref name=elpais_lcdp /> The second part was made available for streaming on 6 April 2018.<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> Pina assessed the viewer experience on Antena 3 versus Netflix as \"very different\", although the essence of the series remained the same.<ref name=elpais_180326>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2018/03/26/television/1522083264_215034.html |title=Por qu\u00e9 \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 ha sido un inesperado \u00e9xito internacional |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=elpais.com |language=es |date=29 March 2018 |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box\n| title = \n| quote = \"[''Money Heist'' had] no promotion or anything. Netflix put it in that pile of series that it has, which is like the sock drawer that you never look in and from which only the algorithm can rescue you, and we didn't think it was a big deal.\"{{hidden begin}}\"Sin promoci\u00f3n ni nada. Netflix la meti\u00f3 en ese mont\u00f3n de series que tiene, que es como el caj\u00f3n de los calcetines que nunca miras y de donde s\u00f3lo te puede rescatar el algoritmo, y no le dimos ninguna importancia.\"{{hidden end}}\n| author = \u2014Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander\n| source = September 2019<ref name=elmundo_190912 />\n| align = right\n| width = 30%\n| bgcolor = lightblue\n}}\n\nWithout a dedicated Netflix marketing campaign,<ref name=elpais_180712 /> the series became the most-watched non-English language series on Netflix in early 2018, within four months of being added to the platform, to the creators' surprise.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s22.q4cdn.com/959853165/files/doc_financials/quarterly_reports/2018/q1/FINAL-Q1-18-Shareholder-Letter.pdf |title=Netflix Q1 2018 Letter to Shareholders |date=16 April 2018 |website=[[Netflix]] Investor Relations |pages=2\u20133 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626162529/https://ir.netflix.com/static-files/419958ac-5fd7-4bcd-9fb1-ebca445a9016 |archivedate=26 June 2018 |url-status=live |access-date=16 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> This prompted Netflix to sign a global exclusive overall deal with Pina shortly afterwards.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/netflix-global-exclusive-overall-deal-la-casa-de-papel-creator-alex-pina-1202871395/ |title=Netflix Signs Global Exclusive Overall Deal with \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 Creator Alex Pina |last=Hopewell |first=John |website=[[variety.com]] |access-date=11 August 2019 |date=12 July 2018}}</ref> Diego \u00c1valos, director of original content for Netflix in Europe, noted that the series was atypical in being watched across many different profile groups.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/08/01/television/1564671328_371797.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 logra m\u00e1s de 34 millones de espectadores y refuerza la estrategia internacional de Netflix |last=Avenda\u00f1o |first=Tom C. |website=elpais.com |language=es |access-date=27 September 2019 |date=2 August 2019}}</ref> Common explanations for the drastic differences in viewership between Antena 3 and Netflix were changed consumption habits of series viewers,<ref name=elpais_180326 /><ref name=elmundo_190912 /> and the [[binge-watching]] potential of streaming.<ref name=lavanguardia_190719 /><ref name=elpais_180326 /> Pina and Sonia Mart\u00ednez of Antena 3 would later say that the series, with its high demand of viewer attention, unknowingly followed the video-on-demand format from the beginning.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Meanwhile, people in Spain would discover the series on Netflix, unaware of its original Antena 3 broadcast.<ref name=elpais_180326 />\n\n=== Renewal ===\n\nIn October 2017, \u00c1lex Pina said that part 2 had remote but intentional spin-off possibilities, and that his team was open to continue the robbers' story in the form of movies or a Netflix renewal.<ref name=elconfidencial_171016>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-10-16/alex-pina-casa-papel-final-ministerio-tiempo-bertin-ursula-corbero_1459636/ |title=El creador de 'La casa de papel' se moja sobre su competencia: 'El Ministerio' y Bert\u00edn |language=es |date=16 October 2017 |website=elconfidencial.com |access-date=15 October 2019}}</ref> Following the show's success on the streaming platform, Netflix approached Pina and Atresmedia to produce new chapters for the originally self-contained story. The writers withdrew themselves for more than two months to decide on a direction,<ref name=sensacine_190617 /> creating a [[Bible (screenwriting)|bible]] with central ideas for new episodes in the process.<ref name=laprensa_190809 /> The crucial factors in accepting Netflix' deal were the creators recognising that characters still had things to say, and having the opportunity to deviate from the perfectly orchestrated heist of the first two parts.<ref name=elcomercio_190808 /> Adamant that the story should be set in Spain again,<ref name=elpais_190614 /> the producers wanted to make it a sequel rather than a direct continuation, and expand on the familiarity and affection between the characters instead of the former group of strangers.<ref name=elperiodico_190718 /> Rio's capture was chosen as the catalyst to get the gang back together, because he as the narrator's boyfriend represented the necessary emotional factor for the renewal not to be \"suicide\".<ref name=elcomercio_190720>{{Cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-temporada-3-trailer-fecha-estreno-sinopsis-personajes-tercera-parte-series-netflix-espana-money-heist-nnda-nnlt-noticia-556069 |title=\"La casa de papel\", temporada 3: fecha de estreno en Netflix, c\u00f3mo ver online, tr\u00e1iler, actores, personajes y cr\u00edtica |language=es |date=20 July 2019 |website=elcomercio.pe |access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nNetflix officially renewed the series for a third part with a considerably increased budget on 18 April 2018,<ref name=elperiodico_190627 /> which might make part 3 the most expensive series per episode in Spanish television history, according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref name=partiv/> As writing was in progress, Pina stated in July 2018 that he appreciated Netflix' decision to make the episodes 45 to 50 minutes of length, as the narrative could be more compressed and international viewers would have more freedom to consume the story in smaller parts.<ref name=elpais_180712 /> With Netflix' new push to improve the quality and appeal of its English-language versions of foreign shows, and over 70 percent of viewers in the United States choosing dubs over subtitles for the series, Netflix hired a new dubbing crew for part 3 and re-dubbed the first two parts accordingly.<ref name=\"nytimes_190719\">{{cite web |first=Jill |last=Goldsmith |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/19/arts/television/netflix-money-heist.html |title=Netflix Wants to Make Its Dubbed Foreign Shows Less Dubby |publisher=[[nytimes.com]] |date=19 July 2019 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref> Part 3, consisting of eight episodes, was released on 19 July 2019;<ref name=\"elcomercio_190808\" /> the first two episodes of part 3 also had a limited theatrical release in Spain one day before.<ref name=\"partiv\" />\n\nIn August 2019, Netflix announced that part 3 was streamed by 34 million household accounts within its first week of release, of which 24 million finished the series within this period,<ref name=variety_190801>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/global/netflix-la-casa-de-papel-money-heist-part-3-smashes-records-1203288791/ |title=Netflix\u2019s \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 \u2013 \u2018Money Heist\u2019 \u2013 Part 3 Smashes Records |last2=Hopewell |first2=John |last=Lang |first=Jamie |work=variety.com |access-date=1 August 2019 |date=1 August 2019}}</ref> thereby making it one of the most-watched productions on Netflix of all time, regardless of language.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/08/02/money-heist-3-smashes-netflix-records-34million-tune-new-episodes-10506673/ |title=Money Heist smashes records as season 3 becomes Netflix's most watched show ever |publisher=metro.co.uk |last=Pierce |first=Tilly |date=2 August 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref> Netflix had an estimated 148 million subscribers world-wide in mid-2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/netflix-la-casa-de-papel-part-3-wows-madrid-world-premiere-1203265758/ |title=Netflix\u2019s \u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 Part 3 Wows at World Premiere |publisher=variety.com |last=Hopewell |first=John |date=12 July 2019 |access-date=2 October 2019}}</ref> In October 2019, Netflix ranked ''Money Heist'' as their third most-watched TV series for the past twelve months,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/17/business/media/netflix-top-ten-movies-tv-shows.html |title=Netflix\u2019s Top 10 Original Movies and TV Shows, According to Netflix |publisher=nytimes.com |last=Koblin |first=John |date=17 October 2019 |access-date=21 October 2019}}</ref> and named it as the most-watched series across several European markets in 2019, including France, Spain and Italy, though not the UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/la-casa-de-papel-money-heist-tops-netflix-charts-europe-1203453375/ |title=\u2018La Casa de Papel\u2019 (\u2018Money Heist\u2019) Tops Netflix\u2019s Charts in Key European Markets |last=Keslassy |first=Elsa |work=variety.com |access-date=1 January 2020 |date=30 December 2019}}</ref> Twitter ranked the show fourth in its \"Top TV shows worldwide\" of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://blog.twitter.com/en_us/topics/insights/2019/ThisHappened-in-2019.html |title=#ThisHappened in 2019 |publisher=blog.twitter.com |last=Filadelfo |first=Elaine |date=9 December 2019 |access-date=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Future ===\n\nFilming of an initially unannounced fourth part ended in August 2019.<ref name=p4filmend>{{cite web |url=https://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/el-profesor-desmiente-su-salida-de-la-casa-de-papel-articulo-880949 |title=El Profesor desmiente su salida de La casa de papel |website=[[elespectador.com]] |date=13 September 2019 |access-date=1 October 2019}}</ref> It will consist of eight episodes.<ref name=\"elcomercio_190808\" /> Netflix announced in December 2019 that part 4 would be released on 3 April 2020;<ref name=netflix_191208>{{cite web |title=\u2018Money Heist\u2019 Season 4 Coming to Netflix in April 2020 |url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/news/money-heist-season-4-renewed-at-netflix-what-we-know-so-far-12-2019/ |website=What's on Netflix |date=December 8, 2019}}</ref> a documentary involving the producers and the cast will premiere on Netflix the same day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Netflix emitir\u00e1 un documental sobre el fen\u00f3meno de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 |url=https://www.fotogramas.es/noticias-cine/a30713079/la-casa-de-papel-documental-netflix/ |author=Silvestre, Juan |website=fotogramas.es |date=30 January 2020 |access-date=30 January 2020 |language=es}}</ref> A trailer first shown during the [[Comic Con Experience]] (CCXP) in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] showed the gang members with and without masks, with Nairobi appearing last,<ref name=elpais_191209 /> indicating she would appear in part 4 and resulting in her name becoming a Trending Topic online, ahead of the series itself.<ref name=eldiario_191209 /> Also at CCXP, a scene from the beginning of part 4 was shown, in which the Professor, still in the woods, flees from the police, jumps over a wall to hide and encounters a menacing bull.<ref name=elpais_191209 /><ref name=eldiario_191209>{{cite web |title=Primera escena de 'La casa de papel 4' y Trending Topic para Nairobi |url=http://vertele.eldiario.es/noticias/La-casa-de-papel-Parte-4-Primera-escena-Nairobi_0_2184381549.html |website=vertele.eldiario.es |date=December 9, 2019 |access-date=9 December 2019 |language=es}}</ref> \u00c1lex Pina and writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander stated that unlike part 3, where the intention was to re-attract the audience with high-energy drama after the move to Netflix, the story of part 4 would unfold slower and be more character-driven.<ref>{{cite web |title=Creadores de La Casa de Papel nos cuentan c\u00f3mo ser\u00e1 la cuarta temporada |url=https://www.estilodf.tv/lo-mas-destacado/creadores-de-la-casa-de-papel-nos-cuentan-como-sera-la-cuarta-temporada |author=Ortiz, Paola |website=estilodf.tv |date=October 4, 2019 |access-date=10 December 2019 |language=es}}</ref> At another occasion, Pina and executive producer Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato teased part 4 as the \"most traumatic [part] of all\" because \"this much tension has to explode somewhere\".<ref name=abc_191215 /> Alba Flores (Nairobi) said the scriptwriters had previously made many concessions to fans in part 3, but would go against audience wishes in part 4 and that \"anyone who loves Nairobi will suffer\".<ref name=elpais_191209 /> According to Pedro Alonso (Berlin), the focus of part 4 will be on saving Nairobi's life and standing by each other to survive.<ref name=elpais_191209>{{cite web |title=\u201cQuien quiera a Nairobi va a sufrir\u201d: El elenco de \u2018La casa de papel\u2019 promete sorpresas en la nueva temporada |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2019/12/09/television/1575911603_998928.html/ |author=Oliveira, Joana |website=elpais.com |date=10 December 2019 |access-date=10 December 2019 |language=es}}</ref> \n\nIn October 2019, the online editions of Spanish newspapers ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' and ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' re-reported claims by the Spanish website {{Interlanguage link|formulatv.com|es|F\u00f3rmula TV}} that Netflix had renewed the series for a fifth part, and that pre-production had already begun.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/cultura/abci-casa-papel-tendra-5-temporada-netflix-201910141657_video.html |title=La casa de papel tendr\u00e1 5\u00aa temporada en Netflix |language=es |date=14 October 2019 |website=abc.es |access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/series/netflix/20191015/47996801852/la-casa-de-papel-netflix-temporada-5.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019, renovada por una quinta temporada en Netflix |language=es |date=15 October 2019 |website=lavanguardia.com |access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.formulatv.com/noticias/netflix-renueva-la-casa-de-papel-quinta-temporada-alvaro-morte-96344/ |title=Netflix renueva 'La Casa de Papel' por una quinta temporada que volver\u00e1 a contar con \u00c1lvaro Morte |language=es |date=14 October 2019 |website=formulatv.com |access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, ''La Vanguardia'' quoted director Jes\u00fas Colmenar's statement \"That there is going to be a fifth [part] can be said\", and that the new part would be filmed after Vancouver Media's new project ''[[Sky Rojo]]''.<ref name=lavanguardia_191117>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/local/sevilla/20191117/471696494420/director-de-la-casa-de-papel-la-cuarta-temporada-va-a-ser-mas-dura-para-el-espectador.html |title=Director de 'La Casa de Papel': \"La cuarta temporada va a ser m\u00e1s dura para el espectador\" |language=es |date=17 November 2019 |website=lavanguardia.com |access-date=17 November 2019 |quote=[Colmenar ha precisado que ''[[Sky Rojo]]''] se producir\u00e1 entre la cuarta y la quinta temporada de ''La Casa de Papel''. \"Que hay quinta temporada s\u00ed se puede decir\", ha concluido entre risas tras ser advertido por [[Pedro Alonso]].}}</ref> Colmenar also stated that there have been discussions with Netflix about creating a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of the series.<ref name=lavanguardia_191117 /> In an interview in December 2019, Pina and Mart\u00ednez Lobato would not discuss the possibility of a fifth part because of confidentiality contracts, and only said that \"Someone knows there will be [a part 5], but we don't.\"<ref name=abc_191215>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-alex-pina-creador-casa-papel-somos-unos-perturbados-autocritica-201912150042_noticia.html |title=\u00c1lex Pina, creador de \u00abLa casa de papel\u00bb: \u00abSomos unos perturbados de la autocr\u00edtica\u00bb |last=Cort\u00e9s |first=Helena |language=es |date=15 December 2019 |website=abc.es |access-date=15 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Public response ===\n\n[[File:Casa_de_Papel_at_Patras_Carnival_(cropped).jpg|thumb|right|240px|[[Cosplay]] in [[Patras]], Greece, in 2019.]]\n\nAfter the move to Netflix, the series remained the most-followed series on Netflix for six consecutive weeks and became one of the most popular series on [[IMDb]].<ref name=elpais_180326 /> It regularly trended on [[Twitter]] world-wide, largely because celebrities commented on it, such as football players [[Neymar]] and [[Marc Bartra]], American singer [[Romeo Santos]],<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> and author [[Stephen King]].<ref name=cnet_190719 /> While users flooded social networks with media of themselves wearing the robbers' outfit,<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> the robbers' costumes were worn at the [[Rio Carnival]], and Dal\u00ed icons were shown on huge banners in [[Saudi Arabia]] football stadiums.<ref name=elpais_180326 /> Real footage of these events would later be shown in part 3 as a tribute to the show's international success.<ref name=abc_190725>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/criticas/abci-casa-papel-3-critica-tercera-temporada-casa-papel-asalto-golpe-billete-nunca-mejor-dicho-201907250839_noticia.html |title=Cr\u00edtica de la tercera temporada de \"La casa de papel\": Asalto a golpe de billete... nunca mejor dicho |last=Jim\u00e9nez |first=Alex |website=abc.es |access-date=28 September 2019 |date=25 June 2019 |language=es}}</ref> The [[Mus\u00e9e Gr\u00e9vin]] in [[Paris]] added statues of the robbers to its wax museum in summer 2018.<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> The show's iconography was used prominently by third parties for advertising,<ref>{{cite AV media |date=24 September 2019 |title=Santa Isabel - La Casa del Ahorro |language=es |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oQAOSJB8ISk |access-date=4 October 2019 |publisher=[[Santa Isabel (supermarkets)|Santa Isabel]] via youtube.com}}</ref> sports presentations,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.am.com.mx/superdeportivo/Robaran-la-Liga-Tlaxcala-FC-presenta-nueva-camiseta-a-La-Casa-de-Papel-20190809-0050.html |title=\u00bfRobar\u00e1n la Liga? Tlaxcala FC presenta nueva camiseta a 'La Casa de Papel' |last=Jim\u00e9nez |first=Alex |website=am.com.mx |access-date=28 September 2019 |date=9 August 2019 |language=es}}</ref> and in porn.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-xvideos-llega-casa-raquel-version-porno-casa-papel-201909271203_noticia.html |title=Llega \"La casa de Raquel\", la versi\u00f3n porno de \"La casa de papel\" |last=Jim\u00e9nez |access-date=4 October 2019 |date=27 September 2019 |language=es}}</ref>\n\nThere have also been negative responses to the influence of the show. In numerous incidents, real heist men wore the show's red costumes and Dal\u00ec masks in their attacks or copied the fictional robbers' infiltration plans.<ref name=newstatesman_180824>{{cite web |url=https://www.newstatesman.com/culture/tv-radio/2018/08/spanish-hit-series-la-casa-de-papel-captures-europe-s-mood-decade-after |title=Spanish hit series \"La Casa de Papel\" captures Europe\u2019s mood a decade after the crash |last=Bock |first=Pauline |website=newstatesman.com |access-date=11 August 2019 |date=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref name=elpais_lcdp /><ref name=abc_190807>{{cite web |url=https://www.abc.es/play/series/noticias/abci-efecto-toxico-casa-papel-201908071042_noticia.html |title=El efecto \"t\u00f3xico\" de \"La casa de papel\"  |last=Zamora |first=I. |website=abc.es |access-date=4 October 2019 |date=7 August 2019 |language=es}}</ref> The robbers' costumes were banned at the 2019 [[Limassol Carnival Festival]] as a security measure as a result.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.euronews.com/2018/11/14/cypriot-carnival-bans-costumes-inspired-by-netflix-series-money-heist |title=Cypriot carnival bans costumes inspired by Netflix series 'Money Heist' |last=Rodriguez Martinez |first=Marta |website=euronews.com |access-date=4 October 2019 |date=14 November 2018 |language=es}}</ref> The series was used in an attack on [[YouTube]], when hackers removed the most-played song in the platform's history, \"[[Despacito]]\", and left an image of the show instead.<ref name=elpais_lcdp /> In unrelated reports, a journalist from the Turkish state channel AkitTV and an Ankaran politician have both warned against the show for supposedly encouraging terrorism and being \"a dangerous symbol of rebellion\".<ref name=newstatesman_180824 />\n\nSpanish newspaper ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'' saw the public response as a reflection of the \"climate of global disenchantment\" where the robbers represent the \"perfect antiheroes\",<ref name=elmundo_190719 /> and ''[[The New Statesman]]'' explained the show's resonance with international audiences as coming from the \"social and economic tensions it depicts, and because of the utopian escape it offers\".<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> Viewer response was especially high in Mediterranean Europe and the Latin world, in particular Spain, [[Italy]], [[France]], [[Portugal]], [[Brazil]], [[Chile]] and [[Argentina]],<ref name=elcomercio_190808 /> so Spanish as a common language did not appear to be a unifying reason for the show's success.<ref name=elmundo_190912 /> Writer Javier G\u00f3mez Santander and actor Pedro Alonso (Berlin) rather argued that the Latin world used to feel at the periphery of global importance, but a new sentiment was coming that Spain could compete with the global players in terms of media production levels and give the rest of the world a voice.<ref name=variety_190801 /><ref name=elmundo_190912 />\n\n=== Critical reception ===\n\nThe series' beginning on Antena 3 was received well by Spanish media.<ref name=larazon_170621 /> Nay\u00edn Costas of ''[[El Confidencial]]'' named the premiere a promising start that captivated viewers with \"adrenaline, well-dosed touches of humor and a lot of tension\", but considered it a challenge to maintain the dramatic tension for the remainder of the series.<ref>{{cite web |last=Costas |first=Nay\u00edn |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-05-02/critica-la-casa-de-papel-serie-antena3-ursula-corbero-alba-flores_1375703/ |title='La casa de papel' sube el list\u00f3n con un impecable, y cinematogr\u00e1fico, piloto |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=2 May 2017 |access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref> While considering the pilot's voice-over narration unnecessary and the sound editing and dialogs lacking, Natalia Marcos of ''[[El Pa\u00eds]]'' enjoyed the show's ensemble cast and the ambition, saying \"It is daring, brazen and entertaining, at least when it starts. Now we want more, which is not little.\"<ref name=elpais_170503 /> Reviewing the full first part, Marcos lauded the series for its outstanding direction, musical selection and for trying to innovate Spanish television, but criticized the length and ebbing tension.<ref name=elpais_171124>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2017/11/24/television/1511480525_162365.html |title=\u2018La casa de papel\u2019 ha ganado |language=es |last=Marcos |first=Natalia |website=[[elpais.com]] |access-date=12 August 2019 |date=24 November 2017}}</ref> At the end of the series' original run, Nay\u00edn Costas of ''El Confidencial'' commended the series for its \"high quality closure\" that may make the finale \"one of the best episodes of the Spanish season\", but regretted that it aimed to satisfy viewers with a predictable happy ending rather than risk to \"do something different, original, ambitious\", and that the show was unable to follow in the footsteps of Pina's ''[[Locked Up (TV series)|Locked Up]]''.<ref name=elconfidencial_171123>{{cite web |last=Costas |first=Nay\u00edn |url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/series-tv/2017-11-23/final-como-acaba-la-casa-de-papel-muerte-berlin-hermano-profesor_1482592/ |title=Final feliz en 'La casa de papel', un gran cap\u00edtulo lastrado por la falta de sorpresa |language=es |publisher=elconfidencial.com |date=23 November 2017 |access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter the show's move to Netflix for its international release, Adrian Hennigan of the Israeli ''[[Haaretz]]'' said the series was \"more of a twisty thriller than soapy telenovela, driven by its ingenious plot, engaging characters, tense flash points, pulsating score and occasional moments of humor\", but taunted the English title \"Money Heist\" as bland.<ref name=haaretz_180807 /> In a scathing review, Pauline Bock of the British magazine ''[[New Statesman]]'' questioned the global hype of the series, saying that it was \"full of plot holes, clich\u00e9d slow-motions, corny love stories and gratuitous sex scenes\", before continuing to add that \"the music is pompous, the voice-over irritating, and it's terribly edited\".<ref name=newstatesman_180824 /> [[John Doyle (critic)|John Doyle]] of ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' praised parts 1 and 2 for the heist genre subversions; he also said that the series could be \"deliciously melodramatic at times\" with \"outrageous twists and much passion\" like a telenovela.<ref name=theglobeandmail>{{cite web |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-three-great-foreign-dramas-on-netflix-for-a-summer-binge/?cmpid=rss1 |title=Three great foreign dramas on Netflix for a summer binge |last=Doyle |first=John |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |access-date=12 August 2019 |date=22 June 2018}}</ref> Jennifer Keishin Armstrong of the [[BBC]] saw the series' true appeal in the interpersonal dramas emerging through the heist between \"the beautiful robbers, their beautiful hostages and the beautiful authorities trying to negotiate with them.\"<ref name=bbc_190312 /> David Hugendick of ''[[Die Zeit]]'' found the series \"sometimes a bit sentimental, a little cartoonesque\", and the drama sometimes too telenovela-like, but \"all with a good sense for timing and spectacle.\"<ref name=zeit_180410>{{cite web |last=Hugendick |first=David |url=https://www.zeit.de/kultur/film/2018-04/haus-des-geldes-serie-netflix |title=Knackt das System! |language=de |publisher=[[zeit.de]] |date=10 April 2018 |access-date=12 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] gave part 3 an approval rating of 100% based on 11 reviews, with an average rating of 7/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"An audacious plan told in a non-linear fashion keeps the third installment moving as ''Money Heist'' refocuses on the relations between its beloved characters.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/la_casa_de_papel/s03 |title=Money Heist: Part 3 (2019) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=18 October 2019}}</ref> While lauding the technical achievements, Javier Zurro of ''[[El Espa\u00f1ol]]'' described the third part as \"first-class entertainment\" that was unable to transcend its roots and lacked novelty. He felt unaffected by the internal drama between the characters and specifically disliked Tokyo's narration for its hollowness.<ref name=elespanol_190724 /> Alex Jim\u00e9nez of Spanish newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' found part 3 mostly succeeding in its attempts to reinvent the show and stay fresh.<ref name=abc_190725 />  Euan Ferguson of ''[[The Guardian]]'' recommended watching part 3, as \"it's still a glorious ''[[Peaky Blinders (TV series)|Peaky Blinders]]'', just with [[tapas]] and subtitles\",<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2019/jul/28/week-in-tv-i-am-nicola-orange-is-new-black-keeping-faith-money-heist |title=The week in TV: I Am Nicola; Orange Is the New Black; Keeping Faith; Money Heist |last=Ferguson |first=Euan |publisher=theguardian.com |access-date=7 October 2019 |date=28 July 2019}}</ref> while Pere Sol\u00e0 Gimferrer of ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' found that the amount of plot holes in part 3 could only be endured with constant [[suspension of disbelief]].<ref name=lavanguardia_190809 /> Though entertained, Alfonso Rivadeneyra Garc\u00eda of Peruvian newspaper ''[[El Comercio (Peru)|El Comercio]]'' said the show does \"what it does best: pretend to be the smartest boy in class when, in fact, it is only the most alive.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elcomercio.pe/tvmas/series/casa-papel-temporada-3-review-resena-spoilers-netflix-ecpm-noticia-654511 |title=\"La casa de papel\" temporada 3: rese\u00f1amos sin SPOILERS los primeros 3 episodios |language=es |last=Rivadeneyra Garc\u00eda |first=Alfonso |publisher=elcomercio.pe |access-date=3 October 2019 |date=19 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards and nominations ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:95%; width:99%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! style=\"width:30%;\" | Category\n! style=\"width:40%;\" | Nominee(s)\n! Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2017\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Premios Feroz]]\n| Best drama series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cita web|title=La lista completa de ganadores de los premios Feroz 2018|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.es/2018/01/22/la-lista-completa-de-ganadores-de-los-premios-feroz-2018_a_23339879/|date=22 January 2018|publisher=huffingtonpost.es|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best leading actress of a series\n| [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best supporting actor in a series\n| [[Paco Tous]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best supporting actress in a series\n| [[Alba Flores]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 19th {{Interlanguage link|Premios IRIS|es|Premios Iris (Espa\u00f1a)}}\n| Best screenplay\n| [[\u00c1lex Pina]], Esther Mart\u00ednez Lobato, David Barrocal, Pablo Roa, Esther Morales, Fernando Sancrist\u00f3bal, Javier G\u00f3mez Santander\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web |title=XIX Premios Iris |url=https://www.academiatv.es/premios/iris-2017/ |access-date=26 October 2019 |website=academiatv.es |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[FesTVal|FesTVal de Televisi\u00f3n y Radios de Vitoria]] \n| Best direction in fiction\n| Jes\u00fas Colmenar, Alejandro Bazzano, Miguel \u00c1ngel Vivas, \u00c1lex Rodrigo\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cita web |url=http://www.festval.tv/amplia/34963/galardones-2017.html |title=FesTVal Vitoria \u00b7 Festival de la Televisi\u00f3n |access-date=16 December 2017 |website=festval.tv |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best fiction (by critics)\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | {{Interlanguage link|68th Fotogramas de Plata|es|Anexo:Fotogramas de Plata 2017}}\n| Best Spanish series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web |title='La casa de papel', mejor serie espa\u00f1ola seg\u00fan los lectores |url=https://www.fotogramas.es/fotogramas-de-plata/a19459528/la-casa-de-papel-mejor-serie-espanola-segun-los-lectores/ |date=25 February 2018 |access-date=26 October 2019 |website=fotogramas.es |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"12\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[46th International Emmy Awards]]\n| Best drama series\n| ''Money Heist''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/international-emmy-awards-winners-list-nevsu-money-heist-man-in-an-orange-shirt-1202505247/ |title='International Emmy Awards: \u2018Money Heist\u2019, \u2018Nevsu\u2019 Among Honorees \u2013 Complete Winners List |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=20 November 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=20 November 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 20th {{Interlanguage link|Premios IRIS|es|Premios Iris (Espa\u00f1a)}}\n| Best actress\n| [[\u00darsula Corber\u00f3]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=XX Premios Iris |url=https://www.academiatv.es/premios/iris-2018/ |publisher=academiatv.es |accessdate=26 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | Premios MiM Series \n| Best direction\n| Jes\u00fas Colmenar, Alejandro Bazzano, Miguel \u00c1ngel Vivas, \u00c1lex Rodrigo\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=larazon_180620>{{cite web |url=https://www.larazon.es/tv-y-comunicacion/tv-